msgctxt "4080_Erena"
msgid "I'm real glad I decided to come to Tokyo."
msgstr "Estoy muy feliz de haberme mudado a Tokio."

msgctxt "4092_Akiyama"
msgid "Why do you say that all of a sudden?"
msgstr "¿Por qué lo dices?"

msgctxt "4104_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I'm just happy that a nice man like you decided to come and request me, that's all."
msgstr "Ah, solo me pone feliz que un buen hombre como usted me haya solicitado, eso era."

msgctxt "4116_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. How long have you been here, anyway?"
msgstr "Ja, ja, ja. Bueno, ¿cuánto tiempo llevas aquí?"

msgctxt "4128_Erena"
msgid "Actually, about 10 days."
msgstr "Llevo como unos diez días."

msgctxt "4140_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? You're probably still getting used to it, then?"
msgstr "¿En serio? Entonces todavía no te acostumbras, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "4152_Erena"
msgid "Yep, but I've already gotten the hang of the pace here."
msgstr "Podría decirse que no, pero ya le voy agarrando el ritmo."

msgctxt "4164_Akiyama"
msgid "The pace? What do you mean?"
msgstr "¿Ritmo? ¿Qué quieres decir?"

msgctxt "4176_Erena"
msgid "How fast people walk."
msgstr "El ritmo con el que camina la gente."

msgctxt "4188_Erena"
msgid "I've always been a fast walker, so I didn't have any trouble fittin' in."
msgstr "Siempre he sido de caminar rápido, así que no ha sido problema para mí."

msgctxt "4200_Erena"
msgid "I think I made the right choice in comin' here."
msgstr "Creo que hice bien al venir aquí."

msgctxt "4212_Akiyama"
msgid "What's your favorite place in Tokyo?"
msgstr "¿Cuál es el lugar que más te gusta de Tokio?"

msgctxt "4224_Erena"
msgid "Well, actually I haven't been able to get around much. Do ya know any fun places to go?"
msgstr "Bueno, no he tenido la oportunidad de conocer bien el lugar. ¿Me podrías recomendar algún lugar para divertirme?"

msgctxt "4236_Akiyama"
msgid "Hm? Well, sure... But everybody has different tastes."
msgstr "¿Eh? Claro, sí... Pero supongo que para gustos, colores."

msgctxt "4248_Akiyama"
msgid "What kind of things do you like? Maybe I can show you around a little bit."
msgstr "¿Qué tipo de lugares te gustan? Tal vez así pueda llevarte a conocer algunos."

msgctxt "4260_Erena"
msgid "Really? That'd be great."
msgstr "¿De verdad? Estaría divertido."

msgctxt "4272_Akiyama"
msgid "Do you want to go sightseeing? Or maybe out eating, or shopping?"
msgstr "¿Pero quieres ir a conocer lugares? ¿O tal vez salir a comer o ir de compras?"

msgctxt "4284_Erena"
msgid "Well, maybe some sightseein' first, then a nice\\r\n"\n"drink afterwards."
msgstr "Bueno, conocer un poco, y después tomar algo."

msgctxt "4296_Akiyama"
msgid "If we can find the time, that'd be nice."
msgstr "Si consigo tiempo libre, por supuesto."

msgctxt "4308_Erena"
msgid "Yeah, I'll be looking forward to it."
msgstr "Sí. Estaré esperando con ansias."

msgctxt "4320_Akiyama"
msgid "You came to Tokyo all by yourself?"
msgstr "¿Viniste a Tokio sola?"

msgctxt "4332_Erena"
msgid "Yep. But my sister will be coming soon, too."
msgstr "Sip, pero mi hermana vendrá pronto."

msgctxt "4344_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh? Is she a college student or something?"
msgstr "¿Ah, sí? ¿Es universitaria o algo así?"

msgctxt "4356_Erena"
msgid "No. She's the same as me."
msgstr "No. Está igual que yo."

msgctxt "4368_Akiyama"
msgid "The same? You mean she's a hostess, too?"
msgstr "¿Igual? ¿O sea que también es una hostess?"

msgctxt "4380_Erena"
msgid "Yeah. We both work at hostess clubs."
msgstr "Sí. Las dos trabajamos en lo mismo."

msgctxt "4392_Akiyama"
msgid "For real?"
msgstr "¿En serio?"

msgctxt "4404_Erena"
msgid "Surprised? Haha."
msgstr "¿Te sorprende? Ja, ja."

msgctxt "4416_Akiyama"
msgid "Sort of. But it's interesting."
msgstr "Más o menos. Pero me parece interesante."

msgctxt "4428_Erena"
msgid "That's not even the craziest part! For a while, we were both workin' at the same club!"
msgstr "¡Y eso ni siquiera es lo mejor! ¡Llegamos a trabajar en el mismo club!"

msgctxt "4440_Akiyama"
msgid "Wow. So is she planning on working here, then?"
msgstr "Vaya, ¿entonces va a venir a trabajar acá?"

msgctxt "4452_Erena"
msgid "Maybe."
msgstr "Tal vez."

msgctxt "4464_Akiyama"
msgid "I guess Kyoto is a bit slower-paced, huh?"
msgstr "Supongo que los lentos son los de Kioto."

msgctxt "4476_Erena"
msgid "They walk so slow! I always get so annoyed when I'm stuck walkin' behind someone."
msgstr "¡Son muy lentos! Me estresa bastante ir detrás de alguien y ver cómo camina tan lento."

msgctxt "4488_Akiyama"
msgid "I know the feeling."
msgstr "Te entiendo."

msgctxt "4500_Erena"
msgid "Of course, people tell me that I walk fast, so that may be part of it."
msgstr "Sí, aunque la gente me dice que soy de caminar rápido, así que puede ser eso."

msgctxt "4512_Akiyama"
msgid "Yeah, if you're a fast walker and most people from Kyoto walk slowly, it must seem especially slow."
msgstr "Puede ser, si de por sí caminas rápido, como camina la gente de Kioto debe ser peor."

msgctxt "4524_Akiyama"
msgid "But Tokyo is just about perfect for you, huh?"
msgstr "Pero Tokio te calza perfecto, ¿no?"

msgctxt "4536_Erena"
msgid "Oh yeah, totally!"
msgstr "¡Ah sí, sin duda!"

msgctxt "4548_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. Sounds like you might fit in better here than at home. When it comes to walking at a fast pace, at least."
msgstr "Me parece que podrías encajar mejor acá que donde vivías, por lo menos si de caminar rápido se trata."

msgctxt "4560_Erena"
msgid "Yeah... But I am gettin' annoyed with the crowds here."
msgstr "Sí... Pero aun así, me molestan las multitudes."

msgctxt "4572_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh, I guess every place has its pros and cons."
msgstr "Supongo que cada lugar tiene sus pros y sus contras."

msgctxt "4584_Erena"
msgid "Um, can I tell you something?"
msgstr "Mm, ¿puedo decirte algo?"

msgctxt "4596_Akiyama"
msgid "Hm?"
msgstr "¿Mm?"

msgctxt "4608_Erena"
msgid "Oh, never mind. Forget I said anything."
msgstr "No, no importa. Olvídalo."

msgctxt "4620_Akiyama"
msgid "Huh? Come on, spit it out."
msgstr "¿Eh? Solo dímelo."

msgctxt "4632_Erena"
msgid "Well, I'm actually seein' someone."
msgstr "Bueno, es que estoy saliendo con alguien."

msgctxt "4644_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh? And you left him back in Kyoto?"
msgstr "¿Ah? ¿Y lo dejaste en Kioto?"

msgctxt "4656_Erena"
msgid "No... He's here."
msgstr "No... Está aquí."

msgctxt "4668_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, did you come to Tokyo to be with him?"
msgstr "Ah, ¿entonces viniste aquí para poder estar con él?"

msgctxt "4680_Erena"
msgid "No. I met him here."
msgstr "No. Lo conocí aquí."

msgctxt "4692_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? But I thought you just got here a little while ago."
msgstr "¿En serio? Pensé que llevabas poco tiempo acá."

msgctxt "4704_Erena"
msgid "I met him the day after I got here!"
msgstr "¡Lo conocí justo el siguiente día de llegar!"

msgctxt "4716_Akiyama"
msgid "You're kidding. That's fast work."
msgstr "No puedes estar hablando en serio. Parece que no eres rápida solo con los pies."

msgctxt "4728_Erena"
msgid "Maybe! But he's real handsome."
msgstr "Puede ser... ¡Pero es muy lindo!"

msgctxt "4740_Akiyama"
msgid "Just your type, huh?"
msgstr "Justo es de tu tipo, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "4752_Erena"
msgid "Well, I thought maybe I was movin' too fast, but..."
msgstr "Bueno, quizá este yendo demasiado rápido, pero..."

msgctxt "4764_Akiyama"
msgid "How did you two meet?"
msgstr "¿Cómo se conocieron?"

msgctxt "4776_Erena"
msgid "Oh, he walked up to me when my friend and I were out drinking."
msgstr "Él se me acercó cuando estaba bebiendo con un amigo."

msgctxt "4788_Akiyama"
msgid "He picked you up, just like that!?"
msgstr "¡¿Te eligió, así como así?!"

msgctxt "4800_Erena"
msgid "I guess he did!<Color:7>"
msgstr "¡Supongo que sí!<Color:7>"

msgctxt "4812_Akiyama"
msgid "And you decided to go out with him?"
msgstr "¿Y decidiste salir con él?"

msgctxt "4824_Erena"
msgid "I guess I like to be flattered. And I'd just arrived in Tokyo, so I was kind of caught up in the excitement."
msgstr "Supongo que me gusta ser halagada. Y así, recién llegada a Tokio, quedé atrapada de la emoción."

msgctxt "4836_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, okay. So, what did you want to say about this guy?"
msgstr "Bueno, está bien. ¿Qué me ibas a decir sobre él?"

msgctxt "4848_Erena"
msgid "Oh, just that we're goin' out."
msgstr "Oh, solo que vamos a salir."

msgctxt "4860_Akiyama"
msgid "Huh? That's it? That's why you're so happy?"
msgstr "¿Solo eso? ¿Por eso estás tan feliz?"

msgctxt "4872_Erena"
msgid "Hehe, yep!"
msgstr "Je, je, ¡sí!"

msgctxt "4884_Akiyama"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "4896_Akiyama"
msgid "What's with young girls these days? I'll never understand what they're thinking."
msgstr "¿Qué pasa con los jóvenes hoy en día? Nunca voy a entender cómo piensan."

msgctxt "4908_Erena"
msgid "Hahah! You're not that old yourself."
msgstr "¡Ja, ja, ja! Tampoco es que seas tan viejo."

msgctxt "4920_Akiyama"
msgid "Hey, I've got one foot in the grave! Well, maybe not in the grave, but I'm within walking distance of the cemetery!"
msgstr "Ya tengo medio pie en la tumba, bueno, puede que en la tumba no cómo tal, pero sí llegando al cementerio."

msgctxt "4932_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! You're funny!"
msgstr "¡Ja, ja, ja! ¡Eres muy gracioso!"

msgctxt "4944_Erena"
msgid "But haven't you ever had an experience like that? Ya know, love at first sight?"
msgstr "Pero, ¿no has tenido alguna vez una experiencia como esa? ¿Amor a primera vista?"

msgctxt "4956_Akiyama"
msgid "Sure I have. When I saw you, for instance."
msgstr "Claro. Cuando te vi, por ejemplo."

msgctxt "4968_Erena"
msgid "Haha! I just told you I had a boyfriend!"
msgstr "¡Ja, ja! ¡Te acabo de decir que tengo novio!"

msgctxt "4980_Akiyama"
msgid "I heard you. What about it?"
msgstr "Sí. ¿Y qué tiene?"

msgctxt "4992_Erena"
msgid "Well, you're gonna have to try harder if ya want me to leave him for you."
msgstr "Bueno, vas a tener que esforzarte más si quieres que lo deje por ti."

msgctxt "5004_Akiyama"
msgid "Is this something you tell all your customers?"
msgstr "¿Le dices eso a todos tus clientes?"

msgctxt "5016_Erena"
msgid "Hm? Is there something wrong with talkin' about it?"
msgstr "¿Mm? ¿Tiene algo de malo?"

msgctxt "5028_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, it is a bit of a downer. I mean, most guys want to at least have the illusion that they come in with."
msgstr "Bueno, es desalentador. La mayoría quieren al menos conservar la misma ilusión con la que entran."

msgctxt "5040_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I guess you're right. Sorry for being so insensitive."
msgstr "Supongo que tienes razón. Perdón por ser tan insensible."

msgctxt "5052_Erena"
msgid "I guess you're just so easy to talk to that I got a little carried away."
msgstr "Supongo que es tan fácil hablar contigo que me dejé llevar un poco."

msgctxt "5064_Akiyama"
msgid "It's all right. I don't mind, personally."
msgstr "No pasa nada, la verdad es que ni me importa."

msgctxt "5076_Erena"
msgid "Oh, that's a relief!"
msgstr "¡Ah, qué alivio!"

msgctxt "5088_Erena"
msgid "I'm so depressed. I wish I could stop thinkin' about this..."
msgstr "Me siento muy mal. Ojalá pudiera dejar de pensar en eso..."

msgctxt "5100_Akiyama"
msgid "What happened?"
msgstr "¿Qué pasó?"

msgctxt "5112_Erena"
msgid "I went shopping yesterday, and I accidentally left the dress I bought behind on the train."
msgstr "Ayer compré un vestido y lo dejé por error en el tren."

msgctxt "5124_Akiyama"
msgid "Ouch..."
msgstr "Ay..."

msgctxt "5136_Erena"
msgid "I'm just so mad at myself. I bought it because I knew my boyfriend would like it."
msgstr "Tengo tanta impotencia. Lo compré porque sabía que le iba a gustar a mi novio."

msgctxt "5148_Erena"
msgid "It was a cute little dress. Cute isn't really my thing, but I thought he'd like it."
msgstr "Era un lindo vestidito. Lo tierno no va conmigo, pero pensé que le gustaría."

msgctxt "5160_Akiyama"
msgid "You choose what you wear depending on who you're with?"
msgstr "¿Eliges tu ropa dependiendo de con quién estás?"

msgctxt "5172_Erena"
msgid "Oh, yeah. I do that all the time!"
msgstr "Ah, sí. ¡Lo hago todo el tiempo!"

msgctxt "5184_Akiyama"
msgid "I guess you can be cute when you try."
msgstr "Supongo que puedes ser linda si lo intentas."

msgctxt "5196_Erena"
msgid "Sure I can."
msgstr "Por supuesto que puedo."

msgctxt "5208_Akiyama"
msgid "Too bad about losing that dress, though."
msgstr "Lamento que hayas perdido ese vestido."

msgctxt "5220_Erena"
msgid "Yeah..."
msgstr "Sí..."

msgctxt "5232_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe your boyfriend could buy you another one."
msgstr "Tal vez tu novio podría comprarte otro."

msgctxt "5244_Erena"
msgid "Well, he doesn't have much money, so..."
msgstr "Bueno, no tiene mucho dinero, así que..."

msgctxt "5256_Akiyama"
msgid "I see. Well, I guess there's nothing wrong with dressing to suit somebody else's taste, but don't go overboard."
msgstr "Bueno, supongo que no hay nada de malo en intentar gustarle a alguien vistiéndose acorde a sus gustos, pero tampoco te excedas."

msgctxt "5268_Akiyama"
msgid "Wouldn't you rather wear something you like?"
msgstr "¿No preferirías ponerte algo que te guste?"

msgctxt "5280_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I don't mind. As long as he likes it, I'm happy."
msgstr "No me importa. Mientras a él le guste, estoy feliz."

msgctxt "5292_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? That's a bit of a surprise."
msgstr "¿De verdad? Me sorprende."

msgctxt "5304_Erena"
msgid "Why? Is that strange?"
msgstr "¿Por qué? ¿Es raro?"

msgctxt "5316_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, it's just that most people tend to go out with people with similar tastes, whether it's fashion, music, or whatever."
msgstr "Ah, es solo que la mayoría de las personas suelen salir con personas con sus mismos gustos, sea de moda, música o lo que sea."

msgctxt "5328_Erena"
msgid "But haven't you ever found yourself growin' to like something that a girlfriend of yours liked?"
msgstr "Pero, ¿alguna vez le ha gustado algo que le gustaba a su pareja?"

msgctxt "5340_Akiyama"
msgid "Huh. Come to think of it, I have. So you mean you're starting to like the kind of clothes that he likes?"
msgstr "Ahora que lo pienso, sí. ¿Entonces lo que intenta decir es que le está empezando a gustar lo que usa su pareja?"

msgctxt "5352_Erena"
msgid "Well... Maybe not quite yet."
msgstr "Bueno... No del todo."

msgctxt "5364_Akiyama"
msgid "I see. I guess there's nothing wrong with dressing to suit somebody else's taste, but don't go overboard."
msgstr "Bueno, supongo que no tiene nada malo gustarle a alguien vistiéndose acorde a sus gustos, pero no hay que pasarse tampoco."

msgctxt "5376_Akiyama"
msgid "I think you've got it wrong."
msgstr "Creo que lo malinterpretaste todo."

msgctxt "5388_Erena"
msgid "Huh? How?"
msgstr "¿Eh? ¿Cómo?"

msgctxt "5400_Akiyama"
msgid "I think most men would be more comfortable with a woman who dresses to suit her own taste, instead of changing herself to match his."
msgstr "Creo que los hombres se sienten más a gusto con una mujer que vista con sus propios gustos en lugar de imitar los de él."

msgctxt "5412_Erena"
msgid "Really?"
msgstr "¿En serio?"

msgctxt "5424_Akiyama"
msgid "If you try too hard at that kind of thing, it'll just make the man feel like he has to try, too."
msgstr "Si fuerzas demasiado este tipo de cosas, solo lo pondrás en la necesidad de hacerlo también."

msgctxt "5436_Erena"
msgid "I see... I don't mind it myself, so it didn't occur to me that it might make other people uncomfortable."
msgstr "Entiendo... A mí no me importa, así que ni se me pasó por la cabeza que pudiera incomodar a otras personas."

msgctxt "5448_Akiyama"
msgid "I guess there's nothing wrong with dressing to impress. Just don't be too harsh on him, all right?"
msgstr "Supongo que no hay nada malo en vestirse para impresionar. Simplemente que no sea algo muy chillón para él, ¿de acuerdo?"

msgctxt "5460_Erena"
msgid "Huh. I had no idea. Thanks."
msgstr "No tenía ni idea. Gracias."

msgctxt "5472_Erena"
msgid "What kind of women do you like?"
msgstr "¿Qué tipo de mujeres te gustan?"

msgctxt "5484_Akiyama"
msgid "Hmm... Well, for starters, Kansai girls are out of the question."
msgstr "Hmm... Bueno, para empezar, las chicas de Kansai están fuera de la discusión."

msgctxt "5496_Erena"
msgid "Huh? You don't like Kansai girls?"
msgstr "¿Eh? ¿No te gustan las chicas de Kansai?"

msgctxt "5508_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. Just kidding."
msgstr "Je, je, je. Estaba bromeando."

msgctxt "5520_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! Don't scare me like that!"
msgstr "¡Ja, ja, ja! ¡No me asustes así!"

msgctxt "5532_Akiyama"
msgid "What about you, Erena? What kind of men do you like?"
msgstr "¿Y tú, Erena? ¿Qué tipo de hombres te gustan?"

msgctxt "5544_Erena"
msgid "Me? Well, I like a man to be confident around other people, but..."
msgstr "¿A mí? Bueno, me gusta que un hombre tenga confianza sin importar la gente, pero..."

msgctxt "5556_Akiyama"
msgid "Yes?"
msgstr "¿Sí?"

msgctxt "5568_Erena"
msgid "I want them to be sweet and needy when it's just\\r\n"\n"the two of us."
msgstr "Quiero que sean dulces y necesitados cuando solo\\r\n"\n"somos nosotros dos."

msgctxt "5580_Erena"
msgid "Oh, and he should be rich. And kind, too."
msgstr "Ah, y debería ser rico. Y amable, también."

msgctxt "5592_Akiyama"
msgid "Rich, huh? At least you're honest."
msgstr "Rico, ¿eh? Al menos eres honesta."

msgctxt "5604_Erena"
msgid "Yep. People are always tellin' me I'm the honest type."
msgstr "Sí. La gente siempre me dice que soy muy honesta."

msgctxt "5616_Akiyama"
msgid "I didn't really mean that as a compliment..."
msgstr "Realmente no quise decir eso como un cumplido..."

msgctxt "5628_Erena"
msgid "Ahahaha! ♪"
msgstr "¡Aja, ja, ja! ♪"

msgctxt "5640_Akiyama"
msgid "So how does your current boyfriend measure up?"
msgstr "Así que, ¿tu novio es una persona con dinero?"

msgctxt "5652_Erena"
msgid "Actually, he doesn't have much money."
msgstr "De hecho, él no tiene mucho dinero."

msgctxt "5664_Akiyama"
msgid "Most people don't."
msgstr "La mayoría de la gente no tiene."

msgctxt "5676_Erena"
msgid "But he's nice, so I don't mind."
msgstr "Pero es bueno conmigo, así que no me importa."

msgctxt "5688_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. That's good."
msgstr "Je, je,. Eso es bueno."

msgctxt "5700_Akiyama"
msgid "Isn't that asking a little much? You don't run into people with all of those qualities very often."
msgstr "¿No es eso pedir demasiado? No te encuentras con personas con todas esas cualidades muy a menudo."

msgctxt "5712_Erena"
msgid "I know! And I've been lookin' real hard, too."
msgstr "¡Lo sé! Y también he estado buscando durante mucho tiempo."

msgctxt "5724_Akiyama"
msgid "I don't know. I think it would be pretty hard for a guy to live up to all of those expectations."
msgstr "No sé. Creo que sería bastante difícil para un hombre estar a la altura de todas esas expectativas."

msgctxt "5736_Erena"
msgid "Yeah... And if I really found a man like that, I think I might get tired tryin' to keep up with him."
msgstr "Sí... Y si realmente encontrara a un hombre así, creo que me cansaría tratando de seguirle el ritmo."

msgctxt "5748_Akiyama"
msgid "Right. You have to find someone who fits your personality."
msgstr "Cierto. Tienes que encontrar a alguien que encaje con tu personalidad."

msgctxt "5760_Erena"
msgid "You're right. In that case, I'd rather just have a handsome guy who won't tire me out."
msgstr "Tienes razón. En ese caso, prefiero estar con un chico guapo que no me canse."

msgctxt "5772_Akiyama"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "5784_Akiyama"
msgid "Why do you like manly men?"
msgstr "¿Por qué te gustan los hombres varoniles?"

msgctxt "5796_Erena"
msgid "Is there something wrong with that?"
msgstr "¿Hay algo malo con eso?"

msgctxt "5808_Akiyama"
msgid "I think I know the type of guy you're talking about, but there's a difference between acting manly and being a real man, you know."
msgstr "Creo que entiendo al tipo de hombre al que te refieres, pero hay una diferencia entre actuar como un hombre de verdad y ser un hombre de verdad."

msgctxt "5820_Akiyama"
msgid "Most of those guys are selfish and arrogant. They don't care about other people."
msgstr "La mayoría de esos tipos son egoístas y arrogantes. No se preocupan por otras personas."

msgctxt "5832_Erena"
msgid "I suppose you're right. A real man wouldn't go around yellin' about little things, would he? I hate that."
msgstr "Supongo que tienes razón. Un hombre de verdad no iría por ahí gritando sobre cualquier pequeñez, ¿cierto? Odio eso."

msgctxt "5844_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh? But I thought you liked that type of guy."
msgstr "¿Ah, sí? Pero pensé que te gustaba ese tipo de hombres."

msgctxt "5856_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! Funny, ain't it?"
msgstr "¡Ja, ja, ja! Irónico, ¿no es así?"

msgctxt "5868_Akiyama"
msgid "You <Italic>are</Italic> kind of contradicting yourself."
msgstr "Tú <Italic>eres</Italic> un poco contradictoria con tus declaraciones."

msgctxt "5880_Erena"
msgid "Hmm... I guess I want a manly man who cares about other people."
msgstr "Hmm... Supongo que quiero un hombre varonil que se preocupe por los demás."

msgctxt "5892_Akiyama"
msgid "You can't get past the manly man part, huh?"
msgstr "No puedes dejar pasar de la parte del hombre varonil, ¿eh?"

msgctxt "5904_Erena"
msgid "Listen, listen! My sister got a pinky ring from her boyfriend."
msgstr "¡Escuchate esto! Mi hermana recibió un anillo en el dedo meñique de su novio."

msgctxt "5916_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh? Pinky rings are cheap, so they're popular among college students and young people. There's nothing very unusual about that, is there?"
msgstr "¿Ah, sí? Los anillos para el dedo meñique son baratos, por lo que son populares entre los estudiantes universitarios y los jóvenes. No hay nada muy inusual en eso, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "5928_Erena"
msgid "No, but it's the <Italic>way</Italic> he gave it to her that's amazin'!"
msgstr "No, ¡pero fue la <Italic>manera</Italic> en la que se lo dió lo que hizo eso increíble!"

msgctxt "5940_Akiyama"
msgid "What do you mean? How did he do it?"
msgstr "¿A qué te refieres? ¿Cómo lo hizo?"

msgctxt "5952_Erena"
msgid "Well, apparently they were at dinner."
msgstr "Bueno, al parecer estaban cenando."

msgctxt "5964_Erena"
msgid "My sister had just started eating her dessert..."
msgstr "Mi hermana estaba empezabando a comer su postre..."

msgctxt "5976_Erena"
msgid "...when she bit down on something hard."
msgstr "... cuando de golpe, mordió algo duro."

msgctxt "5988_Erena"
msgid "That's how she found the ring!"
msgstr "¡Y así ella encontró el anillo!"

msgctxt "6000_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? That must've been a lot of work for him to set up!"
msgstr "¿En serio? ¡Le habrá tomado mucho trabajo armarlo todo!"

msgctxt "6012_Erena"
msgid "I guess he asked the waiter to put the ring in there."
msgstr "Supongo que le pidió al camarero que pusiera el anillo allí."

msgctxt "6024_Akiyama"
msgid "It sounds like he's trying pretty hard."
msgstr "Parece que se está esforzando bastante."

msgctxt "6036_Erena"
msgid "Right?"
msgstr "Right?"

msgctxt "6048_Erena"
msgid "If somebody did something like that for me, I'd melt!"
msgstr "Si alguien hiciera algo así por mí, ¡me derretiría ahí mismo!"

msgctxt "6060_Akiyama"
msgid "He's creative, I'll give him that."
msgstr "Es creativo, le doy un punto por eso."

msgctxt "6072_Erena"
msgid "Why is she always the one who has stuff like that happen to her? It's not fair!"
msgstr "¿Por qué siempre es ella a la que le pasan este tipo de cosas? ¡No es justo!"

msgctxt "6084_Akiyama"
msgid "Hahah. Don't ask me."
msgstr "Ja, ja, ja. A mí no me preguntes."

msgctxt "6096_Erena"
msgid "I'm jealous."
msgstr "Estoy tan celosa."

msgctxt "6108_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, do you want me to give you a present?"
msgstr "Bueno, ¿quieres que te haga un regalo?"

msgctxt "6120_Erena"
msgid "Really? Just remember, you've got to be pretty creative if ya want to impress me."
msgstr "¿De verdad? Recuerda que tienes que ser muy creativo si quieres impresionarme."

msgctxt "6132_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe I should've kept my mouth shut..."
msgstr "Tal vez debería haber mantenido la boca cerrada..."

msgctxt "6144_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe I should try that one myself."
msgstr "Tal vez debería intentarlo yo mismo."

msgctxt "6156_Erena"
msgid "You? Hahahah! That's a good one!"
msgstr "¿Tú? ¡Ja, ja, ja! ¡Esa es buena!"

msgctxt "6168_Erena"
msgid "But I bet the girl would love it."
msgstr "Pero apuesto a que a la chica le encantaría."

msgctxt "6180_Akiyama"
msgid "No, really. I think it's a great idea. I'm going to have to try it sometime."
msgstr "No, hablo en serio. Creo que es una gran idea. Voy a tener que intentarlo alguna vez."

msgctxt "6192_Erena"
msgid "Really? Just keep in mind, rose gold is my favorite."
msgstr "¿De verdad? Solo ten en cuenta que el oro rosado es mi favorito."

msgctxt "6204_Akiyama"
msgid "I didn't say I'd give it to you, did I?"
msgstr "Nunca dije que sería para ti, ¿no es así?"

msgctxt "6216_Erena"
msgid "Oh sure. You've got to keep it a secret or it isn't going to be a surprise. I understand. But I'll be lookin' forward to it."
msgstr "Oh, no pasa nada. Tienes que mantenerlo en secreto o si no, no contaría como una sorpresa. Lo entiendo. Pero estaré deseando que llegue."

msgctxt "6228_Akiyama"
msgid "You're an optimist, aren't you?"
msgstr "Si que eres optimista."

msgctxt "6240_Akiyama"
msgid "I don't know... Putting it in her food? I'm not sure that's such a great idea."
msgstr "No lo sé... ¿Colocarlo en la comida? No estoy seguro de que sea una gran idea."

msgctxt "6252_Erena"
msgid "Huh? Whaddya mean!?"
msgstr "¿Eh? ¡¿Qué quieres decir?!"

msgctxt "6264_Akiyama"
msgid "I mean, it's not very sanitary, is it?"
msgstr "Quiero decir, no es muy seguro que digamos, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "6276_Erena"
msgid "I wouldn't mind."
msgstr "A mí no me importaría."

msgctxt "6288_Akiyama"
msgid "What if she swallows it before she notices it's in there? Or breaks a tooth on it?"
msgstr "¿Qué pasa si se lo traga antes de darse cuenta de que está allí? ¿O si se rompe un diente?"

msgctxt "6300_Erena"
msgid "That wouldn't be good."
msgstr "Eso no terminaría bien."

msgctxt "6312_Akiyama"
msgid "Still, I like the idea of surprising somebody with a present."
msgstr "Aun así, me gusta la idea de sorprender a alguien con un regalo."

msgctxt "6324_Erena"
msgid "I know. I'm so jealous of her."
msgstr "Completamente. Estoy tan celosa de ella."

msgctxt "6336_Akiyama"
msgid "Your eyes sure are big, aren't they?"
msgstr "Realmente tienes unos ojos muy grandes."

msgctxt "6348_Erena"
msgid "Really? Actually, I get told that a lot."
msgstr "¿En serio? De hecho, me lo dicen mucho."

msgctxt "6360_Erena"
msgid "People tell me to stop starin' at them because it feels like they'll be sucked in!"
msgstr "¡La gente me dice que deje de mirarlos porque parece que van a ser absorbidos!"

msgctxt "6372_Akiyama"
msgid "Haha! I think I know what they mean. Your eyes are really cute."
msgstr "¡Ja, ja! Creo que entiendo a dónde van con eso. Tus ojos son realmente lindos."

msgctxt "6384_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I know."
msgstr "Lo sé."

msgctxt "6396_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. You seem happy."
msgstr "Je, je, je. Pareces contenta."

msgctxt "6408_Erena"
msgid "What can I say? I love compliments, even if they aren't true."
msgstr "¿Qué puedo decir? Me encantan los cumplidos, aunque no sean ciertos."

msgctxt "6420_Akiyama"
msgid "Even if it's not true?"
msgstr "¿Aunque no sea cierto?"

msgctxt "6432_Erena"
msgid "I'm too stupid to be able to tell when somebody's lyin' to me anyway."
msgstr "Soy demasiado estúpida para darme cuenta de cuándo alguien me está mintiendo."

msgctxt "6444_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. Stupid people don't say they're stupid."
msgstr "Je, je, je. La gente estúpida no dice abiertamente que lo es."

msgctxt "6456_Erena"
msgid "Really?"
msgstr "¿De verdad?"

msgctxt "6468_Akiyama"
msgid "Sure. They're too stupid to know it."
msgstr "Claro. Son demasiado estúpidos para saberlo."

msgctxt "6480_Erena"
msgid "Haha! Maybe I'm not stupid after all."
msgstr "¡Ja, ja! Quizás no soy estúpida después de todo."

msgctxt "6492_Akiyama"
msgid "Wait, you just noticed that? Maybe I should take back what I just said."
msgstr "Espera, ¿te diste cuenta? Tal vez debería retirar lo dicho."

msgctxt "6504_Erena"
msgid "Hey! That's not fair!"
msgstr "Ey, ¡eso no es justo!"

msgctxt "6516_Akiyama"
msgid "I'm no fan of empty flattery. It's just embarrassing."
msgstr "No soy fanático de los halagos vacíos. Es simplemente vergonzoso."

msgctxt "6528_Erena"
msgid "Really? Don't let me down!"
msgstr "Really? Don't let me down!"

msgctxt "6540_Akiyama"
msgid "I haven't exactly lived a perfect life, so when I hear it, I always think they have an ulterior motive."
msgstr "No he vivido exactamente una vida perfecta que digamos, así que cuando los escucho, siempre pienso que vienen con alguna segunda intención detrás."

msgctxt "6552_Erena"
msgid "That's not true. Yer a great guy!"
msgstr "Eso no es cierto. ¡Eres un buen chico!"

msgctxt "6564_Akiyama"
msgid "Even if I am, the people flattering me can't tell that just by looking at me, can they? They don't know what kind of life I've led."
msgstr "Incluso si lo soy, las personas que simplemente me halagan no pueden saberlo con tan solo mirarme, ¿no es así? No saben qué tipo de vida he llevado."

msgctxt "6576_Akiyama"
msgid "That's particularly true in Kamurocho. You never know what people are up to around here."
msgstr "Eso es algo particularmente cierto en Kamurocho. Nunca se sabe lo que la gente está tramando por aquí."

msgctxt "6588_Erena"
msgid "Really? That's pretty scary..."
msgstr "¿En serio? Eso es bastante aterrador..."

msgctxt "6600_Erena"
msgid "Tokyo can be kind of intimidatin'."
msgstr "Tokio puede ser un poco intimidante."

msgctxt "6612_Akiyama"
msgid "Yep, you sure are pretty."
msgstr "Sip, tu realmente eres guapa."

msgctxt "6624_Erena"
msgid "Ya don't have to go that far. It just makes it sound like you're lyin'."
msgstr "No tienes por qué ir tan lejos. Solamente haces que suene como si estuvieras mintiendo."

msgctxt "6636_Akiyama"
msgid "I thought you said you didn't mind if it wasn't true."
msgstr "Pensé que habías dicho que no te importaba si no era verdad."

msgctxt "6648_Erena"
msgid "Huh!? Ya mean you were lyin'!?"
msgstr "¡¿Eh?! ¡¿Estabas mintiendo?!"

msgctxt "6660_Akiyama"
msgid "What do you think?"
msgstr "¿Qué piensas?"

msgctxt "6672_Erena"
msgid "Hehe, I'm happy either way."
msgstr "Je, je. Soy feliz de todos modos."

msgctxt "6684_Akiyama"
msgid "You just want to be flattered, huh?"
msgstr "Tú solo quieres que te halaguen, ¿eh?"

msgctxt "6696_Erena"
msgid "You look like you're a strong drinker."
msgstr "Parece que eres un bebedor empedernido."

msgctxt "6708_Akiyama"
msgid "I suppose I am."
msgstr "Supongo que lo soy."

msgctxt "6720_Erena"
msgid "Really? Then by all means, drink up! Order something expensive!"
msgstr "¿En serio? Entonces, por supuesto, ¡bebe! ¡Pide algo caro!"

msgctxt "6732_Akiyama"
msgid "What're you saying? The more expensive the drink, the longer you want to take to drink it. You have to really savor it."
msgstr "¿Pero qué dices? Cuanto más cara sea la bebida, más tiempo querrás tardar en beberla. Tienes que saborearla de verdad."

msgctxt "6744_Erena"
msgid "What do you usually like to drink?"
msgstr "¿Qué te suele gustar beber?"

msgctxt "6756_Akiyama"
msgid "Well..."
msgstr "Bueno..."

msgctxt "6768_Akiyama"
msgid "Usually just canned beer. I'll buy some at a convenience store and have a little party by the roadside."
msgstr "Por lo general, solo cerveza en lata. Compraré unas cuantas en una tienda de conveniencia y haré una pequeña fiesta al borde de la carretera."

msgctxt "6780_Erena"
msgid "Wow, that's pretty cool. I've always wanted to try something like that."
msgstr "Wow, eso es genial. Siempre he querido intentar algo así."

msgctxt "6792_Erena"
msgid "I've never been able to drink in public without worrying what people might think."
msgstr "Nunca he podido beber en público sin preocuparme por lo que la gente pueda pensar."

msgctxt "6804_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, why don't you join me next time?"
msgstr "Bueno, ¿por qué no te nos unes la próxima vez?"

msgctxt "6816_Erena"
msgid "Ooh, yes! Definitely gimme a call!"
msgstr "¡Oh, sí! ¡Definitivamente! ¡Tú solo llámame!"

msgctxt "6828_Akiyama"
msgid "It's a date then."
msgstr "Una cita será entonces."

msgctxt "6840_Erena"
msgid "Promise!"
msgstr "¡Es una promesa!"

msgctxt "6852_Akiyama"
msgid "I like shochu. You know, sweet potato liquor?"
msgstr "Me gusta el shochu, el licor de camote. ¿Conoces?"

msgctxt "6864_Erena"
msgid "Really? You like shochu!?"
msgstr "¿De verdad? ¡¿Te gusta el shochu?!"

msgctxt "6876_Akiyama"
msgid "Sure. You too?"
msgstr "Claro. ¿Tú también?"

msgctxt "6888_Erena"
msgid "I love it. It's probably the kind of liquor I drink the most."
msgstr "Me encanta. Probablemente es el tipo de licor que más bebo."

msgctxt "6900_Akiyama"
msgid "It is good, isn't it? It's got a crisp, clear flavor."
msgstr "Es bueno, ¿a que sí? Tiene un sabor crujiente y claro."

msgctxt "6912_Erena"
msgid "But I usually start out with a cocktail, or a cassis orange."
msgstr "Pero normalmente empiezo con un cóctel, o un cassis de naranja."

msgctxt "6924_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? Why?"
msgstr "¿En serio? ¿Por qué?"

msgctxt "6936_Erena"
msgid "I guess it's just because I think I look cute drinkin' them."
msgstr "Tal vez es solo porque creo que me veo linda tomando."

msgctxt "6948_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. I see..."
msgstr "Je, je. Ya veo..."

msgctxt "6960_Akiyama"
msgid "I drink a lot of whiskey. Bourbon, scotch. That kind of thing."
msgstr "Frecuento mucho el whisky. Bourbon, whisky escocés. Ese tipo de cosas."

msgctxt "6972_Erena"
msgid "Wow. Those are some hard drinks. Most girls can't drink that sort of thing."
msgstr "Wow. Esos son tragos fuertes. La mayoría de las chicas no pueden beber ese tipo de cosas."

msgctxt "6984_Akiyama"
msgid "Yeah. I wonder why that is."
msgstr "Sip. Me pregunto el por qué."

msgctxt "6996_Erena"
msgid "Maybe because they're brown?"
msgstr "¿Quizás será porque se ven aburridos?"

msgctxt "7008_Akiyama"
msgid "Haha! That's an interesting theory."
msgstr "¡Ja, ja! Es una teoría interesante."

msgctxt "7020_Erena"
msgid "I mean, maybe we'd like 'em better if they were cute and colorful, like cocktails."
msgstr "Quiero decir, tal vez nos gustarían más si fueran lindos y coloridos, como los cócteles."

msgctxt "7032_Akiyama"
msgid "I see... That actually makes sense. You can be surprisingly perceptive sometimes."
msgstr "Ya veo... Eso realmente tiene sentido. A veces puedes ser sorprendentemente perceptiva."

msgctxt "7044_Erena"
msgid "Surprisingly? I think ya mean incredibly!"
msgstr "¿Sorprendentemente? ¡Querrás decir increíblemente!"

msgctxt "7056_Akiyama"
msgid "Hahahah! All right, incredibly perceptive."
msgstr "¡Ja, ja, ja! Muy bien, increíblemente perceptiva entonces."

msgctxt "7068_Erena"
msgid "It must be nice to go on a date in Tokyo."
msgstr "Debe ser agradable tener una cita en Tokio."

msgctxt "7080_Akiyama"
msgid "Depends on where you go."
msgstr "Depende de a dónde vayas."

msgctxt "7092_Erena"
msgid " But there're lots of romantic spots, aren't there?"
msgstr " Pero hay muchos lugares románticos, ¿no?"

msgctxt "7104_Erena"
msgid "What kind of place would you take me if we were goin' on a date?"
msgstr "¿A qué tipo de lugar me llevarías si fuéramos a una cita?"

msgctxt "7116_Akiyama"
msgid "Well..."
msgstr "Bueno..."

msgctxt "7128_Akiyama"
msgid "Somewhere with beautiful night scenery. I guess that's pretty normal though."
msgstr "A un lugar con hermosos paisajes nocturnos. Pero supongo que eso es bastante normal."

msgctxt "7140_Erena"
msgid "That sounds nice. I love going for a drive at night."
msgstr "Eso suena bien. Me encanta salir a dar un paseo por la noche."

msgctxt "7152_Akiyama"
msgid "Would you like to go with me sometime, then?"
msgstr "¿Entonces, te gustaría ir conmigo alguna vez?"

msgctxt "7164_Erena"
msgid "Sure. Only..."
msgstr "Claro. Pero, una cosa..."

msgctxt "7176_Akiyama"
msgid "What?"
msgstr "¿Qué?"

msgctxt "7188_Erena"
msgid "You make sure ya keep your eyes on the road. I'll be the one enjoying the scenery."
msgstr "Asegúrate de mantener los ojos en la carretera. Así puedo disfrutar del paisaje."

msgctxt "7200_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. All right."
msgstr "Je, je. Muy bien."

msgctxt "7212_Akiyama"
msgid "Someplace with great food. I need to enjoy myself, too."
msgstr "Un lugar con buena comida. Yo también necesito disfrutar."

msgctxt "7224_Erena"
msgid "Haha! That's so like you. But we gotta like the same kinda food then."
msgstr "¡Ja, ja! Eso sí que te pega. Pero nos tiene que gustar el mismo tipo de comida entonces."

msgctxt "7236_Akiyama"
msgid "I'm not much for fancy restaurants. I'm happy just going to a cheap café or something."
msgstr "No soy muy de restaurantes elegantes. Soy feliz con solo ir a un café barato o algo por el estilo."

msgctxt "7248_Akiyama"
msgid "There's a place not too far from here that makes great chicken pilaf."
msgstr "Hay un lugar no muy lejos de aquí que hace un excelente pilaf de pollo."

msgctxt "7260_Erena"
msgid "Yuck! I hate chicken pilaf! It's got green peas in it, for one thing!"
msgstr "¡Puaj! ¡Odio el pilaf de pollo! ¡Tiene guisantes verdes, para empezar!"

msgctxt "7272_Erena"
msgid "Besides, that kinda place doesn't have atmosphere! I'd want someplace more romantic."
msgstr "Además, ¡ese tipo de lugar casi no tiene atmósfera! Me gustaría un lugar más romántico."

msgctxt "7284_Akiyama"
msgid "That's a secret."
msgstr "Eso es un secreto."

msgctxt "7296_Erena"
msgid "Huh? Why?"
msgstr "¿Eh? ¿Por qué?"

msgctxt "7308_Akiyama"
msgid "You'll see when we actually go on a date."
msgstr "Verás cuando realmente tengamos una cita."

msgctxt "7320_Erena"
msgid "Now you got me all curious! That's not fair!"
msgstr "¡Ahora me tienes toda curiosa! ¡No es justo!"

msgctxt "7332_Akiyama"
msgid "Let's see... First, we'll go there. And then there..."
msgstr "Veamos... Primero, iremos allí. Y luego ahí..."

msgctxt "7344_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, and we can't forget to go there. Everybody loves that place..."
msgstr "Ah, y no podemos olvidarnos de ir allí. A todo el mundo le encanta ese lugar..."

msgctxt "7356_Erena"
msgid "Grr... I really wanna know what you're talking about now! Ya gotta take me!"
msgstr "Grr... ¡Realmente quiero saber de qué estás hablando ahora! ¡Tienes que llevarme!"

msgctxt "7368_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh."
msgstr "Je, je, je."

msgctxt "7380_Akiyama"
msgid "How old are you, Erena?"
msgstr "¿Cuántos años tienes, Erena?"

msgctxt "7392_Erena"
msgid "Me? I'll be 25 later this year."
msgstr "¿Yo? Cumpliré los 25 a finales de este año."

msgctxt "7404_Akiyama"
msgid "So you're 24 now."
msgstr "Así que ahora tienes 24."

msgctxt "7416_Erena"
msgid "That's right. I'm getting to the point where my skin is startin' to show its age."
msgstr "Así es. Estoy llegando al punto en el que mi piel empieza a mostrar su edad."

msgctxt "7428_Erena"
msgid "But I'm taking supplements and tryin' to drink plenty of water every day."
msgstr "Pero estoy tomando suplementos y tratando de beber mucha agua todos los días."

msgctxt "7440_Akiyama"
msgid "They say that drinking water is good."
msgstr "Dicen que beber agua ayuda mucho."

msgctxt "7452_Erena"
msgid "I know! I'm trying to drink at least two glasses a day!"
msgstr "¡Lo sé! ¡Estoy tratando de beber al menos dos vasos al día!"

msgctxt "7464_Akiyama"
msgid "Two glasses? That's not very much. I thought you were supposed to drink eight glasses a day."
msgstr "¿Dos vasos? Eso no es mucho. Creí que debías de beber como ocho vasos al día."

msgctxt "7476_Erena"
msgid "Well, I don't like water very much."
msgstr "Bueno, no es como que me guste mucho el agua."

msgctxt "7488_Erena"
msgid "But I'm doin' my best to have at least two glasses every day."
msgstr "Pero estoy haciendo todo lo posible para tomar al menos dos vasos todos los días."

msgctxt "7500_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. So that's your version of trying hard, huh?"
msgstr "Je, je. Así que a eso le llamas esforzarse, ¿eh?"

msgctxt "7512_Erena"
msgid "Yep! Ya gotta give me credit for tryin', at least!"
msgstr "¡Sí! ¡Tienes que darme crédito por intentarlo, al menos!"

msgctxt "7524_Erena"
msgid "If I'm not careful, I'll be thirty before I know it."
msgstr "Si no tengo cuidado, tendré treinta años antes de darme cuenta."

msgctxt "7536_Akiyama"
msgid "That's true. It happened to me."
msgstr "Eso es cierto. A mí me pasó."

msgctxt "7548_Erena"
msgid "Really? Maybe you should start taking some supplements with me."
msgstr "¿De verdad? Tal vez deberías empezar a tomar algunos suplementos conmigo."

msgctxt "7560_Akiyama"
msgid "Heh, I'll think about it."
msgstr "Je, me lo pensaré."

msgctxt "7572_Akiyama"
msgid "You don't need it. Your skin looks perfect."
msgstr "No los necesitas. Tu piel luce perfecta."

msgctxt "7584_Erena"
msgid "Oh no. You're just sayin' that."
msgstr "No. Solo estás hablando por hablar."

msgctxt "7596_Akiyama"
msgid "No, I mean it."
msgstr "No, lo digo en serio."

msgctxt "7608_Erena"
msgid "Thanks, but I can't wait till things start going bad. I have to act now, while there's still time."
msgstr "Gracias, pero no puedo esperar a que las cosas empiecen a ir mal. Tengo que actuar ahora, mientras todavía hay tiempo."

msgctxt "7620_Akiyama"
msgid "I suppose that's true."
msgstr "Supongo que tienes un punto."

msgctxt "7632_Erena"
msgid "Course it is! That's why I'm doin' my best to make sure my skin stays this way!"
msgstr "¡Claro que sí! ¡Es por eso que estoy haciendo todo lo posible para asegurarme de que mi piel permanezca así!"

msgctxt "7644_Akiyama"
msgid "Good luck."
msgstr "Buena suerte."

msgctxt "7656_Akiyama"
msgid "It takes more than just water. You have to make sure you eat well, too."
msgstr "Se necesita más que solo agua. También tienes que asegurarte de comer bien."

msgctxt "7668_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I know. I'm not on a diet or anything."
msgstr "Lo sé. No estoy a dieta ni nada parecido."

msgctxt "7680_Akiyama"
msgid "But you think it's okay to drink as much alcohol as you want?"
msgstr "¿Pero crees que está bien beber todo el alcohol que quieras?"

msgctxt "7692_Erena"
msgid "Well, that's true. I think I drink more alcohol than water!"
msgstr "Bueno, eso es verdad. ¡Creo que bebo más alcohol que agua!"

msgctxt "7704_Akiyama"
msgid "That can't be good for your skin, can it?"
msgstr "Eso seguramente no es bueno para tu piel, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "7716_Erena"
msgid "Even if it isn't, I can't very well have this job and not drink, can I?"
msgstr "Incluso si no lo es, no puedo tener este trabajo y no beber, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "7728_Erena"
msgid "I wonder if there're any drinks that are good for your skin too..."
msgstr "Me pregunto si hay algún trago que también sea bueno para la piel..."

msgctxt "7740_Erena"
msgid "I really like Tokyo."
msgstr "Me gusta mucho Tokio."

msgctxt "7752_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh? Why?"
msgstr "¿Sí? ¿Por qué?"

msgctxt "7764_Erena"
msgid "Well, because people walk faster here."
msgstr "Bueno, porque aquí la gente camina más rápido."

msgctxt "7776_Akiyama"
msgid "Yeah, you said that before."
msgstr "Sí, lo habías mencionado antes."

msgctxt "7788_Erena"
msgid "I think it's partly because Kyoto's full of tourists."
msgstr "Creo que en parte se debe a que Kioto está llena de turistas."

msgctxt "7800_Erena"
msgid "This may sound bad, but they walk so slowly that I just wanna kill them sometimes!"
msgstr "Esto puede sonar mal, ¡pero caminan tan lento que a veces me dan ganas de matarlos!"

msgctxt "7812_Akiyama"
msgid "Yeah. If you're sightseeing, you're going to want to take your time and see everything."
msgstr "Sip. Si estás haciendo turismo, es normal que quieras tomarte tu tiempo y verlo todo."

msgctxt "7824_Erena"
msgid "Plus, I'm the high-strung type, so if I get stuck behind somebody, I get real annoyed."
msgstr "Además, me pongo nerviosa fácilmente, así que si me quedo atrapada detrás de alguien, pierdo el control."

msgctxt "7836_Akiyama"
msgid "You're that high-strung?"
msgstr "¿Así de nerviosa eres?"

msgctxt "7848_Erena"
msgid "Yeah... My family keeps tellin' me to slow down and relax."
msgstr "Sí... Mi familia sigue diciéndome que vaya más despacio y me relaje."

msgctxt "7860_Akiyama"
msgid "If your family says that, you must really be bad. You'd think they'd be used to it by now."
msgstr "Si hasta tu familia dice eso, realmente es algo serio. Uno pensaría que ya estarían acostumbrados."

msgctxt "7872_Erena"
msgid "Do you prefer girls who are more laid-back?"
msgstr "¿Prefieres a las chicas que son más relajadas?"

msgctxt "7884_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, I don't know."
msgstr "Bueno, eso no lo sé."

msgctxt "7896_Erena"
msgid "Which is it?"
msgstr "¿Y cuál es?"

msgctxt "7908_Erena"
msgid "The laid-back type, right?"
msgstr "El de tipo relajada, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "7920_Erena"
msgid "Yeah, I thought so. Figured ya like girls who are a little more laid-back."
msgstr "Sip, eso me temía. Imaginé que te gustan las chicas que son un poco más relajadas."

msgctxt "7932_Akiyama"
msgid "You certainly are high-strung. You can't even wait for me to answer your question!"
msgstr "Ciertamente, estás muy nerviosa. ¡Ni siquiera puedes esperar a que responda a tu pregunta!"

msgctxt "7944_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! You're right. I got it bad."
msgstr "¡Ja, ja, ja! Tienes razón. Me lo tomé a mal."

msgctxt "7956_Akiyama"
msgid "I don't really care either way. I could like both types of girls."
msgstr "Realmente no me importa de ninguna manera. Me podrían gustar los dos tipos de chicas."

msgctxt "7968_Erena"
msgid "Really? That's pretty open-minded of you."
msgstr "¿Lo dices en serio? Bastante flexible de tu parte."

msgctxt "7980_Akiyama"
msgid "What about you? You prefer high-strung men, I suppose?"
msgstr "¿Y tú? ¿Prefieres a los hombres enojones, supongo?"

msgctxt "7992_Erena"
msgid "You're right..."
msgstr "Usted tiene razón..."

msgctxt "8004_Erena"
msgid "I just can't deal with men who are too laid-back."
msgstr "Simplemente no puedo lidiar con hombres que están demasiado tranquilos."

msgctxt "8016_Erena"
msgid "I'd probably get annoyed with him any time we walked somewhere together."
msgstr "Probablemente me molestaría con él cada vez que camináramos juntos a algún lugar."

msgctxt "8028_Akiyama"
msgid "I see."
msgstr "Ya veo."

msgctxt "8040_Akiyama"
msgid "Of course I do. I think most men probably like women who are a little laid-back."
msgstr "Claro que sí. Creo que a la mayoría de los hombres probablemente les gustan las mujeres que son un poco relajadas."

msgctxt "8052_Erena"
msgid "Yeah, I thought so. Men seem to like that kind of thing."
msgstr "Sí, eso pensaba. A los hombres parece gustarles ese tipo de cosas."

msgctxt "8064_Erena"
msgid "That's why I try not to let 'em see how high-strung I am."
msgstr "Es por eso que trato de que no vean lo nerviosa que soy."

msgctxt "8076_Akiyama"
msgid "You can do that?"
msgstr "¿Se puede hacer eso?"

msgctxt "8088_Erena"
msgid "Sometimes it's tricky. I can get kinda stressed out."
msgstr "A veces es complicado. Puede pasarme factura el estrés después de todo."

msgctxt "8100_Erena"
msgid "Ugh. What should I do?"
msgstr "Ugh. ¿Qué debería hacer?"

msgctxt "8112_Erena"
msgid "Ugh, this is so annoying..."
msgstr "Uf, esto me fastidia demasiado..."

msgctxt "8124_Akiyama"
msgid "What is it? Did I do something wrong?"
msgstr "¿Pasa algo? ¿Hice algo mal?"

msgctxt "8136_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I'm sorry. It's got nothing to do with you. It's just my sister..."
msgstr "Lamento eso. No tiene nada que ver contigo. Es solo que mi hermana..."

msgctxt "8148_Akiyama"
msgid "What about her?"
msgstr "¿Qué pasa con ella?"

msgctxt "8160_Erena"
msgid "She came to Tokyo recently, and we've been living together."
msgstr "Ella vino a Tokio hace poco y hemos estado viviendo juntas."

msgctxt "8172_Akiyama"
msgid "I see. And you're already fighting?"
msgstr "Ya veo. ¿Y te peleas con ella o algo?"

msgctxt "8184_Erena"
msgid "Well... I don't know if I'd call it a fight, exactly. She's just bein' a big baby."
msgstr "Este... No diría que peleamos, exactamente. Es solo que ella está siendo muy infantil."

msgctxt "8196_Akiyama"
msgid "Haha."
msgstr "Ja, ja."

msgctxt "8208_Erena"
msgid "I've been running myself ragged gettin' everything ready for her, but she won't lift a finger."
msgstr "He estado haciendo malabares para prepararlo todo para ella, pero ella no mueve ni un dedo."

msgctxt "8220_Erena"
msgid "It isn't new, of course."
msgstr "Esto no es algo nuevo, por supuesto."

msgctxt "8232_Akiyama"
msgid "It sounds like you're having fun. I bet you like being with her a lot better than living alone."
msgstr "Parece que te estás divirtiendo. Apuesto a que te gusta estar con ella mucho más que vivir sola."

msgctxt "8244_Erena"
msgid "Well, to tell ya the truth..."
msgstr "Bueno, en realidad..."

msgctxt "8256_Erena"
msgid "It's not that fun."
msgstr "No es divertido, para nada."

msgctxt "8268_Akiyama"
msgid "No? But you haven't seen your sister for quite a while, right?"
msgstr "¿No? Pero hace bastante tiempo que no ves a tu hermana, ¿no es así?"

msgctxt "8280_Erena"
msgid "That's true, but... Oh, maybe I'm just tired."
msgstr "Es verdad, pero... Oh, tal vez solo estoy cansada."

msgctxt "8292_Akiyama"
msgid "Don't push yourself too hard. But you're her big sister and you've been in Tokyo longer, so you should try and help her out a bit."
msgstr "No te esfuerces demasiado. Eres su hermana mayor y llevas más tiempo en Tokio, así que deberías intentar ayudarla un poco."

msgctxt "8304_Erena"
msgid "I suppose you're right..."
msgstr "Si usted lo dice..."

msgctxt "8316_Akiyama"
msgid "You must be tired. You can get irritable when you're tired."
msgstr "Debes estar cansada. Puedes ponerte irritable cuando estás cansada."

msgctxt "8328_Erena"
msgid "Hmm. Maybe I am. I've had to deal with her and my boyfriend, too."
msgstr "Hmm. Tal vez sea eso. He tenido que lidiar con ella y también con mi novio."

msgctxt "8340_Akiyama"
msgid "And you're living in unfamiliar surroundings. You could try going back to Kyoto for a visit."
msgstr "Y vives en un entorno desconocido. Podrías intentar volver a Kioto y hacer una visita."

msgctxt "8352_Erena"
msgid "That's true. I'm not exactly homesick, but I would like to see my family again."
msgstr "Es cierto. No soy exactamente nostálgica, pero me gustaría volver a ver a mi familia."

msgctxt "8364_Erena"
msgid "But I can't leave now. Not when my sister just came all the way here to be with me."
msgstr "Pero no puedo irme ahora. No cuando mi hermana vino hasta aquí para estar conmigo."

msgctxt "8376_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, right... Well, how about going on a little sightseeing tour of Tokyo together, then?"
msgstr "Oh, cierto... Bueno, ¿qué tal si hacemos un pequeño recorrido turístico por Tokio juntos, qué dices?"

msgctxt "8388_Erena"
msgid "You're right. I think I'll sleep on it."
msgstr "Tienes razón. Será mejor que piense en algo."

msgctxt "8400_Akiyama"
msgid "You should make up with her. You're living together, after all."
msgstr "Deberías intentar hacer las paces con ella. Al fin y al cabo, viven juntas."

msgctxt "8412_Erena"
msgid "You're right. But we actually get along pretty well most of the time."
msgstr "Tienes razón. Pero en realidad nos llevamos bastante bien la mayor parte del tiempo."

msgctxt "8424_Akiyama"
msgid "You just want a little more consideration."
msgstr "Solo quieres un poco más de consideración."

msgctxt "8436_Erena"
msgid "That's it. She's a big girl now. She should be able to take care of herself－it's for her own good."
msgstr "Eso es todo. Ahora es una niña grande. Debería ser capaz de cuidar de sí misma, es por su propio bien."

msgctxt "8448_Akiyama"
msgid "You sound like a surprisingly good big sister."
msgstr "Suenas como una hermana mayor sorprendentemente buena."

msgctxt "8460_Erena"
msgid "I knew you'd understand."
msgstr "Sabía que lo entenderías."

msgctxt "8472_Erena"
msgid "Speakin' of which, my sister said she wanted to go shopping. Maybe I'll go with her."
msgstr "Hablando de eso, mi hermana dijo que quería ir de compras. A lo mejor me voy con ella."

msgctxt "8484_Akiyama"
msgid "By the way, how are things with your boyfriend?"
msgstr "Por cierto, ¿cómo van las cosas con tu novio?"

msgctxt "8496_Erena"
msgid "Hmm..."
msgstr "Mmm..."

msgctxt "8508_Erena"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "8520_Erena"
msgid "Okay, I guess."
msgstr "Van bien, supongo."

msgctxt "8532_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? That's not the impression I'm getting."
msgstr "¿Segura? Esa no es la impresión que me estás dando."

msgctxt "8544_Erena"
msgid "You're pretty perceptive."
msgstr "Eres bastante perceptivo."

msgctxt "8556_Akiyama"
msgid "You're just easy to read."
msgstr "Eres fácil de leer."

msgctxt "8568_Erena"
msgid "Hahah. Yes, I'm not a very good liar."
msgstr "Ja, ja. Sí, no soy buena mintiendo."

msgctxt "8580_Akiyama"
msgid "Hehe. So I take it things aren't going very well?"
msgstr "Je, je. ¿Debo asumir que las cosas no van tan bien a lo esperado?"

msgctxt "8592_Erena"
msgid "Well... Maybe I jumped into this relationship a little too quickly."
msgstr "Solo... Tal vez me lancé a esta relación demasiado rápido."

msgctxt "8604_Akiyama"
msgid "I told you so. I mean, he just picked you up off the street, right? You didn't really know him at all."
msgstr "Te lo dije. Quiero decir, te acaba de recoger de la calle, ¿verdad? Realmente no lo conocías de nada."

msgctxt "8616_Erena"
msgid "That's true. But he sure seemed like a nice guy at first."
msgstr "Es verdad. Pero al principio parecía un buen tipo."

msgctxt "8628_Akiyama"
msgid "What about now? Now that you know him a little better, do you think he's not for you, or are you still not sure?"
msgstr "¿Y ahora? Ahora que lo conoces un poco mejor, ¿crees que no es para ti, o todavía no estás segura?"

msgctxt "8640_Erena"
msgid "Hmm. I'm not sure. But I also don't see things gettin' much better in the future."
msgstr "Hmm. No estoy segura. Pero tampoco veo que las cosas mejoren mucho en el futuro."

msgctxt "8652_Akiyama"
msgid "I see. Then maybe you're better off just ending it now."
msgstr "Comprendo. Entonces tal vez sea mejor que lo termines ahora."

msgctxt "8664_Erena"
msgid "Yeah. I'm gonna give it a little more thought."
msgstr "Sí. Voy a pensarlo un poco más."

msgctxt "8676_Erena"
msgid "Thanks for listening to me. I can't talk about this with my sister, so it helped a lot."
msgstr "Gracias por escucharme. No puedo hablar de esto con mi hermana, ayuda mucho desahogarme así."

msgctxt "8688_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe you're just working too hard at it. You were buying clothes just to suit his taste after all."
msgstr "Tal vez estés trabajando demasiado duro en ello. Al fin y al cabo, estabas comprando ropa para satisfacer sus gustos."

msgctxt "8700_Akiyama"
msgid "If the other person doesn't react the way you hoped, sometimes it can be disappointing."
msgstr "Si la otra persona no reacciona de la manera que esperabas, a veces puede ser decepcionante."

msgctxt "8712_Erena"
msgid "You really are perceptive."
msgstr "Tú si que eres perceptivo."

msgctxt "8724_Erena"
msgid "That's it exactly. I always do my best to change myself to match my boyfriends' tastes, but in the end I just get tired of it."
msgstr "Eso es exactamente. Siempre hago lo mejor que puedo para cambiarme a mí misma para que coincida con los gustos de mis novios, pero al final me canso de eso."

msgctxt "8736_Akiyama"
msgid "I see..."
msgstr "Ya veo..."

msgctxt "8748_Erena"
msgid "But at least I've got you!"
msgstr "¡Pero al menos te tengo a ti!"

msgctxt "8760_Akiyama"
msgid "Hm? What do you mean?"
msgstr "¿Mmm? ¿A qué se refiere?"

msgctxt "8772_Erena"
msgid "Even if I break up with him, I can always start seein' you, right?"
msgstr "Incluso si rompo con él, siempre puedo empezar a verte, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "8784_Akiyama"
msgid "Hey! So I'm like your insurance policy or something?"
msgstr "¡Eh! ¿Ahora soy como tu póliza de seguro o algo así?"

msgctxt "8796_Akiyama"
msgid "Are you breaking up with him already?"
msgstr "¿Ya vas a romper con él?"

msgctxt "8808_Erena"
msgid "Oh. That... I haven't decided."
msgstr "Oh. Este... No lo he decidido."

msgctxt "8820_Akiyama"
msgid "So it hasn't gotten that bad yet, huh? Still, sometimes it's better to end things quickly rather than having them drag on forever."
msgstr "Así que todavía no se ha ido todo por la borda, ¿eh? Aún así, a veces es mejor terminar las cosas de una vez en lugar de que se prolonguen para siempre."

msgctxt "8832_Erena"
msgid "I just don't know. Should I break up with him?"
msgstr "Simplemente no lo sé. ¿Debería romper con él?"

msgctxt "8844_Akiyama"
msgid "How about you break up with your boyfriend and start going out with me?"
msgstr "¿Qué tal si rompes con tu novio y comienzas a salir conmigo?"

msgctxt "8856_Erena"
msgid "I'm sorry, but I'm not in the mood for that kind of joke right now."
msgstr "Lo siento, pero no estoy de humor para ese tipo de bromas en este momento."

msgctxt "8868_Akiyama"
msgid "Who's joking?"
msgstr "¿Quién está bromeando?"

msgctxt "8880_Erena"
msgid "Do you mind if I ask you something?"
msgstr "¿Te importa si te pregunto algo?"

msgctxt "8892_Akiyama"
msgid "Hm? What?"
msgstr "¿Eh? ¿Qué cosa?"

msgctxt "8904_Erena"
msgid "A while ago my boyfriend and I were watching a DVD. It was a horror movie."
msgstr "Hace un tiempo mi novio y yo estábamos viendo un DVD. Era una película de terror."

msgctxt "8916_Erena"
msgid "Anyway, I was eating a big plate of stir-fried noodles while we were watchin'."
msgstr "De todos modos, estaba comiendo un gran plato de fideos salteados mientras la veíamos."

msgctxt "8928_Akiyama"
msgid "Noodles, huh?"
msgstr "Con que fideos, ¿eh?"

msgctxt "8940_Erena"
msgid "My boyfriend seemed real shocked that I could eat while watching that kinda movie."
msgstr "Mi novio parecía realmente sorprendido de que pudiera comer mientras veía esa película."

msgctxt "8952_Erena"
msgid "You think that's such a strange thing to do?"
msgstr "¿A tí te parece raro eso?"

msgctxt "8964_Akiyama"
msgid "That's not such a big deal. It wouldn't bother me at all."
msgstr "Tampoco es para tanto. No me molestaría en absoluto."

msgctxt "8976_Erena"
msgid "Really? But I should've known better."
msgstr "¿En serio? Debería de haberme dado cuenta."

msgctxt "8988_Akiyama"
msgid "He's a jerk if he's going to make a big deal about something little like that."
msgstr "Sería realmente un imbécil si arma un gran alboroto por un detallito como ese."

msgctxt "9000_Erena"
msgid "Ya really think so?"
msgstr "¿En serio, lo crees?"

msgctxt "9012_Akiyama"
msgid "Yeah, it's really nothing to get upset about."
msgstr "Sí, realmente no es nada para enojarse."

msgctxt "9024_Erena"
msgid "Oh, okay. I'll try and forget about it then."
msgstr "Ah, entiendo. Trataré de no pensar en ello."

msgctxt "9036_Akiyama"
msgid "I'd be a little surprised too. Noodles don't exactly go well with horror movies, if you know what I mean."
msgstr "A mí también me descolocaría un poco. Los fideos no van tan bien que digamos con las películas de terror, si sabes a lo que me refiero."

msgctxt "9048_Erena"
msgid "Really!? Ya think so too?"
msgstr "¡¿Tu crees?! ¡¿De verdad piensas eso?!"

msgctxt "9060_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, it's just my opinion, but..."
msgstr "Bueno, es solo mi opinión, pero..."

msgctxt "9072_Erena"
msgid "I'll just have to not eat anything while we're watching DVDs. Hope I can stand the hunger."
msgstr "Supongo que no comeré nada mientras veamos películas. Espero poder aguantar el hambre."

msgctxt "9084_Akiyama"
msgid "Why don't you just skip the horror films from now on?"
msgstr "¿Por qué no pruebas con otras películas a partir de ahora?"

msgctxt "9096_Akiyama"
msgid "It must've been a pretty boring movie. If he was focused on the movie, he wouldn't even have noticed what you were doing."
msgstr "De seguro que fue una película bastante aburrida. Si él se hubiera concentrado en la película, ni siquiera se habría dado cuenta de lo que estabas haciendo."

msgctxt "9108_Erena"
msgid "Well, it's true that it wasn't very good, but..."
msgstr "Bueno, es cierto que no fue muy buena, pero aún así..."

msgctxt "9120_Akiyama"
msgid "You don't really notice the person next to you in the movie theater when they're eating popcorn, right? It's the same thing."
msgstr "Es como cuando ni prestas atención a la persona que está a tu lado en el cine cuando está comiendo palomitas de maíz, ¿no te parece? Es lo mismo."

msgctxt "9132_Erena"
msgid "Yeah, I think I know what you mean! It always bothers me before the movie starts, but once the lights go down, I can just tune it right out."
msgstr "¡Sí, entiendo para donde vas! Siempre me molesta que hagan eso antes de que comience la película, pero una vez que apagan las luces, puedo volver a la normalidad."

msgctxt "9144_Akiyama"
msgid "Exactly. I think the problem was the movie you were watching."
msgstr "Exactamente. Creo que el problema era la película que estabas viendo."

msgctxt "9156_Erena"
msgid "I see! I've got to go rent a different DVD and see what happens."
msgstr "¡Ya veo! Iré a alquilar un DVD diferente y ver como sale todo."

msgctxt "9168_Erena"
msgid "But I don't want it to be too interesting. Then I'll forget about eatin'."
msgstr "Pero no quiero que sea demasiado interesante. Porque si no, me olvidaré de comer."

msgctxt "9180_Akiyama"
msgid "Do you cook at home much?"
msgstr "¿Tu cocinas mucho en casa?"

msgctxt "9192_Erena"
msgid "Cook?"
msgstr "¿Cocinar?"

msgctxt "9204_Erena"
msgid "I may not look it, but I actually cook a lot."
msgstr "Puede que no lo parezca, pero en realidad cocino mucho."

msgctxt "9216_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. Why do you look so happy?"
msgstr "Heheh. Why do you look so happy?"

msgctxt "9228_Erena"
msgid "I like it when people are surprised I can cook."
msgstr "I like it when people are surprised I can cook."

msgctxt "9240_Erena"
msgid "It's better if you look like you can't cook. Then people are more impressed when they find out that ya can."
msgstr "It's better if you look like you can't cook. Then people are more impressed when they find out that ya can."

msgctxt "9252_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh, I see."
msgstr "Je, je, je. Ya veo."

msgctxt "9264_Erena"
msgid "Makes sense, right?"
msgstr "Makes sense, right?"

msgctxt "9276_Akiyama"
msgid "It's great when women can cook. They become pretty popular, too."
msgstr "It's great when women can cook. They become pretty popular, too."

msgctxt "9288_Erena"
msgid "Yeah, I think I'd do just fine in that department. I even got all my own pots and pans."
msgstr "Yeah, I think I'd do just fine in that department. I even got all my own pots and pans."

msgctxt "9300_Erena"
msgid "People tell me I make a pretty good omurice. Oh, and I make a mean hamburg steak, too."
msgstr "People tell me I make a pretty good omurice. Oh, and I make a mean hamburg steak, too."

msgctxt "9312_Akiyama"
msgid "Really... That's good."
msgstr "Really... That's good."

msgctxt "9324_Erena"
msgid "I know. Maybe I'll whip something up for ya sometime."
msgstr "I know. Maybe I'll whip something up for ya sometime."

msgctxt "9336_Akiyama"
msgid "Sure. It's been a long time since I've last had a home-cooked meal."
msgstr "Sure. It's been a long time since I've last had a home-cooked meal."

msgctxt "9348_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! I was just kiddin' about that last part. Sorry!"
msgstr "Hahahah! I was just kiddin' about that last part. Sorry!"

msgctxt "9360_Akiyama"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "9372_Akiyama"
msgid "So you try to look like you can't cook? What's wrong with letting people know that you can cook right from the beginning?"
msgstr "So you try to look like you can't cook? What's wrong with letting people know that you can cook right from the beginning?"

msgctxt "9384_Erena"
msgid "Bein' all ladylike isn't really my style."
msgstr "Bein' all ladylike isn't really my style."

msgctxt "9396_Akiyama"
msgid "Hey, I thought Kyoto girls were supposed to be elegant."
msgstr "Hey, I thought Kyoto girls were supposed to be elegant."

msgctxt "9408_Erena"
msgid "Oh, come on. Ya know girls from Kyoto aren't really like that, right?"
msgstr "Oh, come on. Ya know girls from Kyoto aren't really like that, right?"

msgctxt "9420_Akiyama"
msgid "I see..."
msgstr "Ya veo..."

msgctxt "9432_Akiyama"
msgid "You can't fool me. I know what you're really like."
msgstr "You can't fool me. I know what you're really like."

msgctxt "9444_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! Don't say that. You'll gimme a bad reputation."
msgstr "Hahahah! Don't say that. You'll gimme a bad reputation."

msgctxt "9456_Erena"
msgid "But now that you know that I can cook, I bet you've changed your opinion of me, haven't ya?"
msgstr "But now that you know that I can cook, I bet you've changed your opinion of me, haven't ya?"

msgctxt "9468_Akiyama"
msgid "I suppose I have. I like you even more now."
msgstr "I suppose I have. I like you even more now."

msgctxt "9480_Erena"
msgid "Ooh, I like the sound of that. Go on..."
msgstr "Ooh, I like the sound of that. Go on..."

msgctxt "9492_Akiyama"
msgid "I'd like to try your cooking sometime."
msgstr "I'd like to try your cooking sometime."

msgctxt "9504_Erena"
msgid "That's going to have to wait till we know each other a bit more. I don't cook for just anybody, ya know."
msgstr "That's going to have to wait till we know each other a bit more. I don't cook for just anybody, ya know."

msgctxt "9516_Erena"
msgid "My little sister went to a flea market the other day and ran into one of her friends from high school! She was sellin' some things there."
msgstr "My little sister went to a flea market the other day and ran into one of her friends from high school! She was sellin' some things there."

msgctxt "9528_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh? And?"
msgstr "Oh? And?"

msgctxt "9540_Erena"
msgid "Then she looked at what her friend was selling..."
msgstr "Then she looked at what her friend was selling..."

msgctxt "9552_Akiyama"
msgid "What was it?"
msgstr "¿Qué era?"

msgctxt "9564_Erena"
msgid "Well, she was sellin' a picture frame that my sister'd given her for her birthday!"
msgstr "Well, she was sellin' a picture frame that my sister'd given her for her birthday!"

msgctxt "9576_Akiyama"
msgid "Ouch. That's not very nice."
msgstr "Ouch. That's not very nice."

msgctxt "9588_Erena"
msgid "No, it isn't. I think it's terrible."
msgstr "No, it isn't. I think it's terrible."

msgctxt "9600_Akiyama"
msgid "Yep. That's not bein' nice at all, if ya ask me."
msgstr "Yep. That's not bein' nice at all, if ya ask me."

msgctxt "9612_Erena"
msgid "Haha! I think you're startin' to sound like me!"
msgstr "Haha! I think you're startin' to sound like me!"

msgctxt "9624_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. Maybe your accent is starting to rub off on me."
msgstr "Heheh. Maybe your accent is starting to rub off on me."

msgctxt "9636_Erena"
msgid "I just love it when people from Tokyo try and talk using the Kansai accent."
msgstr "I just love it when people from Tokyo try and talk using the Kansai accent."

msgctxt "9648_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? Why?"
msgstr "¿En serio? ¿Por qué?"

msgctxt "9660_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I dunno. It's just cute."
msgstr "Oh, I dunno. It's just cute."

msgctxt "9672_Akiyama"
msgid "Don't some people hate fake Kansai accents though? I mean, doesn't it irritate people from Kansai?"
msgstr "Don't some people hate fake Kansai accents though? I mean, doesn't it irritate people from Kansai?"

msgctxt "9684_Akiyama"
msgid "I've heard some people say that they don't want people from Tokyo trying to speak like them."
msgstr "I've heard some people say that they don't want people from Tokyo trying to speak like them."

msgctxt "9696_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I guess some people are like that."
msgstr "Oh, I guess some people are like that."

msgctxt "9708_Erena"
msgid "But I think it's adorable when people make all kindsa mistakes tryin' to speak it."
msgstr "But I think it's adorable when people make all kindsa mistakes tryin' to speak it."

msgctxt "9720_Akiyama"
msgid "So you do think I'm bad at it?"
msgstr "So you do think I'm bad at it?"

msgctxt "9732_Erena"
msgid "Don't feel bad. I wouldn't want ya to get any better at it than ya are."
msgstr "Don't feel bad. I wouldn't want ya to get any better at it than ya are."

msgctxt "9744_Akiyama"
msgid "I think I'll quit using it..."
msgstr "I think I'll quit using it..."

msgctxt "9756_Akiyama"
msgid "There's nothing cute about a Kansai accent. I could maybe understand if it was a girl speaking it, but a man?"
msgstr "There's nothing cute about a Kansai accent. I could maybe understand if it was a girl speaking it, but a man?"

msgctxt "9768_Erena"
msgid "Really? Why do you think that?"
msgstr "Really? Why do you think that?"

msgctxt "9780_Akiyama"
msgid "I've always thought the Kansai accent sounded kind of harsh. It sounds like you're always angry."
msgstr "I've always thought the Kansai accent sounded kind of harsh. It sounds like you're always angry."

msgctxt "9792_Akiyama"
msgid "Sometimes young punks try to fake a Kansai accent. They think it makes them sound tough. I hate it."
msgstr "Sometimes young punks try to fake a Kansai accent. They think it makes them sound tough. I hate it."

msgctxt "9804_Erena"
msgid "Wow. I can't believe you don't appreciate the Kansai accent like I do... I'm kind of shocked."
msgstr "Wow. I can't believe you don't appreciate the Kansai accent like I do... I'm kind of shocked."

msgctxt "9816_Akiyama"
msgid "Lemme take ya out to eat!"
msgstr "Lemme take ya out to eat!"

msgctxt "9828_Erena"
msgid "Haha! You're getting pretty good!"
msgstr "Haha! You're getting pretty good!"

msgctxt "9840_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? That was good?"
msgstr "Really? That was good?"

msgctxt "9852_Erena"
msgid "Well, to me, there isn't anything special about people from Kansai speaking in a Kansai accent. It just sounds natural."
msgstr "Well, to me, there isn't anything special about people from Kansai speaking in a Kansai accent. It just sounds natural."

msgctxt "9864_Erena"
msgid "But when I see somebody from Tokyo tryin' so hard to do it, it's just adorable."
msgstr "But when I see somebody from Tokyo tryin' so hard to do it, it's just adorable."

msgctxt "9876_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. I see."
msgstr "Je, je, je. Ya veo."

msgctxt "9888_Erena"
msgid "Uh-oh. I'm starvin'."
msgstr "Uh-oh. I'm starvin'."

msgctxt "9900_Akiyama"
msgid "You haven't eaten recently?"
msgstr "You haven't eaten recently?"

msgctxt "9912_Erena"
msgid "I ate, but it wasn't enough."
msgstr "I ate, but it wasn't enough."

msgctxt "9924_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. Dieting, are you?"
msgstr "Heheh. Dieting, are you?"

msgctxt "9936_Erena"
msgid "No, it isn't that. I may not look it, but I'm actually a pretty big eater."
msgstr "No, it isn't that. I may not look it, but I'm actually a pretty big eater."

msgctxt "9948_Erena"
msgid "I had a normal meal, but I guess it wasn't enough for me today."
msgstr "I had a normal meal, but I guess it wasn't enough for me today."

msgctxt "9960_Akiyama"
msgid "You eat that much?"
msgstr "You eat that much?"

msgctxt "9972_Erena"
msgid "Yeah. Everybody who knows me says I got a huge appetite."
msgstr "Yeah. Everybody who knows me says I got a huge appetite."

msgctxt "9984_Akiyama"
msgid "You certainly don't look it."
msgstr "You certainly don't look it."

msgctxt "9996_Erena"
msgid "I know! I'm so small that everybody's always shocked when they find out."
msgstr "I know! I'm so small that everybody's always shocked when they find out."

msgctxt "10008_Akiyama"
msgid "Are you a picky eater?"
msgstr "Are you a picky eater?"

msgctxt "10020_Erena"
msgid "Not really. I just hate green peas."
msgstr "Not really. I just hate green peas."

msgctxt "10032_Akiyama"
msgid "Hmm... They say that your parents' eating habits can have a big effect on you."
msgstr "Hmm... They say that your parents' eating habits can have a big effect on you."

msgctxt "10044_Akiyama"
msgid "If your parents aren't picky eaters, you're more likely to grow up eating a large variety of food."
msgstr "If your parents aren't picky eaters, you're more likely to grow up eating a large variety of food."

msgctxt "10056_Erena"
msgid "Oh yeah?"
msgstr "Ya veo."

msgctxt "10068_Akiyama"
msgid "It sounds like you'd make a good mother someday."
msgstr "It sounds like you'd make a good mother someday."

msgctxt "10080_Erena"
msgid "Really? Thanks!"
msgstr "¿En serio? ¡Gracias!"

msgctxt "10092_Akiyama"
msgid "But you'll have to work on eating peas."
msgstr "But you'll have to work on eating peas."

msgctxt "10104_Erena"
msgid "Ugh... That's one thing I can't do."
msgstr "Ugh... That's one thing I can't do."

msgctxt "10116_Akiyama"
msgid "You want something to eat? I can order you something."
msgstr "You want something to eat? I can order you something."

msgctxt "10128_Erena"
msgid "Huh? Really?"
msgstr "¿Eh? ¿En serio?"

msgctxt "10140_Akiyama"
msgid "Sure. Order whatever you like."
msgstr "Sure. Order whatever you like."

msgctxt "10152_Erena"
msgid "You're so nice! Maybe I'll have some <Color:7>Dried Ray Fin<Color:Default>!"
msgstr "You're so nice! Maybe I'll have some <Color:7>Dried Ray Fin<Color:Default>!"

msgctxt "10164_Erena"
msgid "Excuse me!"
msgstr "¡Disculpe!"

msgctxt "10188_Erena"
msgid "真っ黒中。フラグ立てたりWdrResetしたり。"
msgstr "真っ黒中。フラグ立てたりWdrResetしたり。"

msgctxt "10224_Erena"
msgid "That was great!"
msgstr "That was great!"

msgctxt "10236_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. Feeling better now?"
msgstr "Heheh. Feeling better now?"

msgctxt "10248_Erena"
msgid "Thank you!"
msgstr "¡Gracias!"

msgctxt "10260_Akiyama"
msgid "You eat pretty fast, don't you?"
msgstr "You eat pretty fast, don't you?"

msgctxt "10272_Erena"
msgid "Teehee. ♪ Yep!"
msgstr "Teehee. ♪ Yep!"

msgctxt "10284_Erena"
msgid "People say I should enter a speed eatin' contest."
msgstr "People say I should enter a speed eatin' contest."

msgctxt "10296_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe you could slow down just a bit."
msgstr "Maybe you could slow down just a bit."

msgctxt "10308_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, sorry. I don't have enough money."
msgstr "Oh, lo siento. No tengo suficiente dinero..."

msgctxt "10320_Erena"
msgid "What!? Really? But you look like a guy who has lotsa money."
msgstr "What!? Really? But you look like a guy who has lotsa money."

msgctxt "10332_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. Sorry. Maybe next time."
msgstr "Heheh. Sorry. Maybe next time."

msgctxt "10344_Erena"
msgid "Gah... I shouldn't have gotten my hopes up. Now I'm hungrier than before."
msgstr "Gah... I shouldn't have gotten my hopes up. Now I'm hungrier than before."

msgctxt "10356_Akiyama"
msgid "You'll just have to grin and bear it for now. They say you shouldn't eat your fill anyway."
msgstr "You'll just have to grin and bear it for now. They say you shouldn't eat your fill anyway."

msgctxt "10368_Erena"
msgid "But I'm not even close to being full. My stomach's halfway empty, and it's gettin' worse!"
msgstr "But I'm not even close to being full. My stomach's halfway empty, and it's gettin' worse!"

msgctxt "10380_Akiyama"
msgid "Snacking isn't good for you, you know. It's better if you eat more at each meal."
msgstr "Snacking isn't good for you, you know. It's better if you eat more at each meal."

msgctxt "10392_Erena"
msgid "Really? But I want to eat now... What should I do?"
msgstr "Really? But I want to eat now... What should I do?"

msgctxt "10404_Akiyama"
msgid "Wait until your next meal."
msgstr "Wait until your next meal."

msgctxt "10416_Erena"
msgid "Seriously!? But I'm starvin'..."
msgstr "Seriously!? But I'm starvin'..."

msgctxt "10428_Erena"
msgid "Oh no... I just remembered something terrible."
msgstr "Oh no... I just remembered something terrible."

msgctxt "10440_Akiyama"
msgid "What?"
msgstr "¿Qué?"

msgctxt "10452_Erena"
msgid "I met someone I know from Kyoto a little while ago. She was in Tokyo for some sightseeing."
msgstr "I met someone I know from Kyoto a little while ago. She was in Tokyo for some sightseeing."

msgctxt "10464_Akiyama"
msgid "I see. Did something happen between you two?"
msgstr "I see. Did something happen between you two?"

msgctxt "10476_Erena"
msgid "Well... To tell you the truth, she's someone I didn't really want to see."
msgstr "Well... To tell you the truth, she's someone I didn't really want to see."

msgctxt "10488_Akiyama"
msgid "Huh..."
msgstr "Huh..."

msgctxt "10500_Akiyama"
msgid "Did she steal a boyfriend from you or something?"
msgstr "Did she steal a boyfriend from you or something?"

msgctxt "10512_Erena"
msgid "No, nothin' like that. I used to know her in junior high."
msgstr "No, nothin' like that. I used to know her in junior high."

msgctxt "10524_Akiyama"
msgid "I see. What do you think?"
msgstr "I see. What do you think?"

msgctxt "10536_Erena"
msgid "Sorry, but could we change the subject?"
msgstr "Sorry, but could we change the subject?"

msgctxt "10548_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, uh, sure... I'm sorry. I didn't mean to be so insensitive."
msgstr "Oh, uh, sure... I'm sorry. I didn't mean to be so insensitive."

msgctxt "10560_Akiyama"
msgid "Did she used to bully you or something?"
msgstr "Did she used to bully you or something?"

msgctxt "10572_Erena"
msgid "Well... Yeah, that's basically it."
msgstr "Well... Yeah, that's basically it."

msgctxt "10584_Akiyama"
msgid "I see. I can understand why you wouldn't want to see her then."
msgstr "I see. I can understand why you wouldn't want to see her then."

msgctxt "10596_Erena"
msgid "She used to be my friend in junior high, but somewhere along the line she started bullyin' me.  I don't have the slightest clue why."
msgstr "She used to be my friend in junior high, but somewhere along the line she started bullyin' me.  I don't have the slightest clue why."

msgctxt "10608_Akiyama"
msgid "She just started bullying you all of a sudden?"
msgstr "She just started bullying you all of a sudden?"

msgctxt "10620_Erena"
msgid "Yeah. We used to get along fine, too."
msgstr "Yeah. We used to get along fine, too."

msgctxt "10632_Akiyama"
msgid "Then she probably wasn't too happy to see you, either.\\r\n"\n"How did she seem when you saw her?"
msgstr "Then she probably wasn't too happy to see you, either.\\r\n"\n"How did she seem when you saw her?"

msgctxt "10644_Erena"
msgid "Well, normal, I guess. Maybe she forgot what she did to me."
msgstr "Well, normal, I guess. Maybe she forgot what she did to me."

msgctxt "10656_Akiyama"
msgid "I see... Maybe she didn't really mean to bully you at all."
msgstr "I see... Maybe she didn't really mean to bully you at all."

msgctxt "10668_Erena"
msgid "Are you saying I was just imagining it? I don't know."
msgstr "Are you saying I was just imagining it? I don't know."

msgctxt "10680_Akiyama"
msgid "You should use this as an opportunity to get over what happened to you in the past."
msgstr "You should use this as an opportunity to get over what happened to you in the past."

msgctxt "10692_Erena"
msgid "Yeah... Maybe you're right. Ya know, I do feel a little better just talking to you about it. Thanks. <Color:7>♥<Color:Default>"
msgstr "Yeah... Maybe you're right. Ya know, I do feel a little better just talking to you about it. Thanks. <Color:7>♥<Color:Default>"

msgctxt "10704_Akiyama"
msgid "Sorry. I didn't mean to pry. Anyway, cheer up, okay?"
msgstr "Sorry. I didn't mean to pry. Anyway, cheer up, okay?"

msgctxt "10716_Erena"
msgid " Oh, it isn't that big of deal..."
msgstr " Oh, it isn't that big of deal..."

msgctxt "10728_Erena"
msgid "Actually, having you be so considerate about it makes me feel even worse."
msgstr "Actually, having you be so considerate about it makes me feel even worse."

msgctxt "10740_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? Then can I ask what the problem is?"
msgstr "Really? Then can I ask what the problem is?"

msgctxt "10752_Erena"
msgid "Well, she and I used to be friends in junior high, but..."
msgstr "Well, she and I used to be friends in junior high, but..."

msgctxt "10764_Akiyama"
msgid "Mhm."
msgstr "Mhm."

msgctxt "10776_Erena"
msgid "No, I'm sorry. There's no point bothering you with this. Maybe we should change the subject."
msgstr "No, I'm sorry. There's no point bothering you with this. Maybe we should change the subject."

msgctxt "10788_Akiyama"
msgid "All right."
msgstr "Está bien."

msgctxt "10800_Akiyama"
msgid "Did you say you have any brothers or sisters?"
msgstr "Did you say you have any brothers or sisters?"

msgctxt "10812_Erena"
msgid "Actually, I've got three."
msgstr "Actually, I've got three."

msgctxt "10824_Akiyama"
msgid "Wow! That's a lot."
msgstr "Wow! That's a lot."

msgctxt "10836_Erena"
msgid "That's not all. They're all girls!"
msgstr "That's not all. They're all girls!"

msgctxt "10848_Akiyama"
msgid "You've got three sisters!? Seriously?"
msgstr "You've got three sisters!? Seriously?"

msgctxt "10860_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! Yep, I'm serious."
msgstr "Hahahah! Yep, I'm serious."

msgctxt "10872_Erena"
msgid "I'm the oldest."
msgstr "I'm the oldest."

msgctxt "10884_Akiyama"
msgid "Wow. I didn't know that."
msgstr "Wow. I didn't know that."

msgctxt "10896_Akiyama"
msgid "That's a little scary."
msgstr "That's a little scary."

msgctxt "10908_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! Bet you can't even imagine what it's like livin' in our house."
msgstr "Hahahah! Bet you can't even imagine what it's like livin' in our house."

msgctxt "10920_Akiyama"
msgid "It must be a little hard on your father."
msgstr "It must be a little hard on your father."

msgctxt "10932_Erena"
msgid "I think it is. Poor Dad."
msgstr "I think it is. Poor Dad."

msgctxt "10944_Akiyama"
msgid "Yeah... I don't think I could live in an environment like that."
msgstr "Yeah... I don't think I could live in an environment like that."

msgctxt "10956_Erena"
msgid "It can be a little noisy with so many girls in the house, but it's also lotsa fun!"
msgstr "It can be a little noisy with so many girls in the house, but it's also lotsa fun!"

msgctxt "10968_Akiyama"
msgid "Your parents must've worked hard."
msgstr "Your parents must've worked hard."

msgctxt "10980_Erena"
msgid "Haha! In more ways than one..."
msgstr "Haha! In more ways than one..."

msgctxt "10992_Erena"
msgid "My dad kept joking that they'd keep tryin' till they had a boy, but in the end they had all girls."
msgstr "My dad kept joking that they'd keep tryin' till they had a boy, but in the end they had all girls."

msgctxt "11004_Akiyama"
msgid "I can understand how he must feel. Wouldn't you like to have at least one brother?"
msgstr "I can understand how he must feel. Wouldn't you like to have at least one brother?"

msgctxt "11016_Erena"
msgid "Yeah, I guess it woulda been nice to have a brother."
msgstr "Yeah, I guess it woulda been nice to have a brother."

msgctxt "11028_Akiyama"
msgid "Heh, I suppose so."
msgstr "Heh, I suppose so."

msgctxt "11040_Akiyama"
msgid "I can imagine how noisy that'd be. Four girls, all talking in Kansai accents!"
msgstr "I can imagine how noisy that'd be. Four girls, all talking in Kansai accents!"

msgctxt "11052_Erena"
msgid "It's not that bad. You make it sound like the neighbors would be complainin' or something."
msgstr "It's not that bad. You make it sound like the neighbors would be complainin' or something."

msgctxt "11064_Erena"
msgid "We get along pretty well, so there wasn't much fighting. We're four refined Kyoto girls."
msgstr "We get along pretty well, so there wasn't much fighting. We're four refined Kyoto girls."

msgctxt "11076_Akiyama"
msgid "But aren't all families in Kansai kind of noisy?"
msgstr "But aren't all families in Kansai kind of noisy?"

msgctxt "11088_Erena"
msgid "Now just a minute! That's just a stereotype! Not everybody from Kansai is some kind of loudmouth!"
msgstr "Now just a minute! That's just a stereotype! Not everybody from Kansai is some kind of loudmouth!"

msgctxt "11100_Akiyama"
msgid "Really?"
msgstr "¿De verdad?"

msgctxt "11112_Erena"
msgid "We're not like those comedians you see on TV, ya know. That's a little insultin'."
msgstr "We're not like those comedians you see on TV, ya know. That's a little insultin'."

msgctxt "11124_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh. Sorry..."
msgstr "Oh. Sorry..."

msgctxt "11136_Erena"
msgid "I was watching TV with my sister yesterday."
msgstr "I was watching TV with my sister yesterday."

msgctxt "11148_Erena"
msgid "They were talkin' about how long it takes for people to get serious with someone after the first date."
msgstr "They were talkin' about how long it takes for people to get serious with someone after the first date."

msgctxt "11160_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh? And?"
msgstr "Oh? And?"

msgctxt "11172_Erena"
msgid "It seems like a lot of people take forever to make a move."
msgstr "It seems like a lot of people take forever to make a move."

msgctxt "11184_Erena"
msgid "Most of the people on the show seemed to think that was the right approach to take, too."
msgstr "Most of the people on the show seemed to think that was the right approach to take, too."

msgctxt "11196_Erena"
msgid "It got me thinkin' about what the best approach was..."
msgstr "It got me thinkin' about what the best approach was..."

msgctxt "11208_Akiyama"
msgid "That can be a difficult decision."
msgstr "That can be a difficult decision."

msgctxt "11220_Erena"
msgid "Do you like to make your move right away? Or do ya like to take your time?"
msgstr "Do you like to make your move right away? Or do ya like to take your time?"

msgctxt "11232_Akiyama"
msgid "If I like someone, I tell them right away. If you wait too long, somebody else could swoop in and steal them from you."
msgstr "If I like someone, I tell them right away. If you wait too long, somebody else could swoop in and steal them from you."

msgctxt "11244_Erena"
msgid "Really? That's a bit of a surprise."
msgstr "¿De verdad? Me sorprende."

msgctxt "11256_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? Why?"
msgstr "¿En serio? ¿Por qué?"

msgctxt "11268_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I don't know. You seem like the reserved type, so I thought you'd take your time with something like this."
msgstr "Oh, I don't know. You seem like the reserved type, so I thought you'd take your time with something like this."

msgctxt "11280_Akiyama"
msgid "So you prefer that kind of guy?"
msgstr "So you prefer that kind of guy?"

msgctxt "11292_Erena"
msgid "Maybe..."
msgstr "Tal vez..."

msgctxt "11304_Akiyama"
msgid "I like to take my time. You can't hurry love, as they say."
msgstr "I like to take my time. You can't hurry love, as they say."

msgctxt "11316_Erena"
msgid "Haha! I knew it!"
msgstr "Haha! I knew it!"

msgctxt "11328_Erena"
msgid "I figured you'd be that kind of guy."
msgstr "I figured you'd be that kind of guy."

msgctxt "11340_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? I give you that kind of impression?"
msgstr "Really? I give you that kind of impression?"

msgctxt "11352_Erena"
msgid "Yep. I prefer men who take their time."
msgstr "Yep. I prefer men who take their time."

msgctxt "11364_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. I see."
msgstr "Je, je, je. Ya veo."

msgctxt "11376_Akiyama"
msgid "It depends on the situation. The best time to make a move varies from person to person."
msgstr "It depends on the situation. The best time to make a move varies from person to person."

msgctxt "11388_Akiyama"
msgid "If I don't think the time is right, I might wait. Or I might go ahead and make my move if it is."
msgstr "If I don't think the time is right, I might wait. Or I might go ahead and make my move if it is."

msgctxt "11400_Erena"
msgid "But you do make your move sooner or later, right?"
msgstr "But you do make your move sooner or later, right?"

msgctxt "11412_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, sure. You don't meet the right woman very often, after all. You can't let her get away."
msgstr "Well, sure. You don't meet the right woman very often, after all. You can't let her get away."

msgctxt "11424_Erena"
msgid "That's what I thought. There's something a little wild about ya, ain't there?"
msgstr "That's what I thought. There's something a little wild about ya, ain't there?"

msgctxt "11436_Erena"
msgid "So what should I do when the time comes?"
msgstr "So what should I do when the time comes?"

msgctxt "11448_Akiyama"
msgid "Um, did you think I was talking about you?"
msgstr "Um, did you think I was talking about you?"

msgctxt "11460_Erena"
msgid "I didn't think it. I knew it."
msgstr "I didn't think it. I knew it."

msgctxt "11472_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. We'll see about that."
msgstr "Heheh. We'll see about that."

msgctxt "11484_Erena"
msgid "Remember what I told ya about before?"
msgstr "Remember what I told ya about before?"

msgctxt "11496_Akiyama"
msgid "Huh? What're you talking about?"
msgstr "¿Eh? ¿De qué está hablando?"

msgctxt "11508_Erena"
msgid "You know. How I'm good at cooking."
msgstr "You know. How I'm good at cooking."

msgctxt "11520_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh right. What about it?"
msgstr "Oh right. What about it?"

msgctxt "11532_Erena"
msgid "I just ordered a pressure cooker through mail-order."
msgstr "I just ordered a pressure cooker through mail-order."

msgctxt "11544_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh. That's nice."
msgstr "Oh. That's nice."

msgctxt "11556_Erena"
msgid "This should make my cooking even better than before."
msgstr "This should make my cooking even better than before."

msgctxt "11568_Akiyama"
msgid "You keep making me fall for you all over again. I love a woman who can cook."
msgstr "You keep making me fall for you all over again. I love a woman who can cook."

msgctxt "11580_Erena"
msgid "Of course ya do. Pretty soon, I'll practically be a pro."
msgstr "Of course ya do. Pretty soon, I'll practically be a pro."

msgctxt "11592_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. I'll have to go to your house to eat, then."
msgstr "Heheh. I'll have to go to your house to eat, then."

msgctxt "11604_Erena"
msgid "Are you sure you're talkin' about food?"
msgstr "Are you sure you're talkin' about food?"

msgctxt "11616_Akiyama"
msgid "Huh? What do you mean by that?"
msgstr "Huh? What do you mean by that?"

msgctxt "11628_Erena"
msgid "Oh, you know, ya naughty boy."
msgstr "Oh, you know, ya naughty boy."

msgctxt "11640_Akiyama"
msgid "You buy things through mail-order, huh?"
msgstr "You buy things through mail-order, huh?"

msgctxt "11652_Erena"
msgid "All the time! I've bought all kinds of stuff through mail-order."
msgstr "All the time! I've bought all kinds of stuff through mail-order."

msgctxt "11664_Akiyama"
msgid "Really? Somehow I didn't think you'd do that kind of thing. For some reason I imagined you in a department store, fighting over bargains."
msgstr "Really? Somehow I didn't think you'd do that kind of thing. For some reason I imagined you in a department store, fighting over bargains."

msgctxt "11676_Erena"
msgid "You're just being silly. I love buyin' stuff through the mail. All ya got to do is pick up the phone and call the number on the screen."
msgstr "You're just being silly. I love buyin' stuff through the mail. All ya got to do is pick up the phone and call the number on the screen."

msgctxt "11688_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, I thought you meant that you bought it online. But you're talking about one of those home shopping shows, right? Yeah, they're fun."
msgstr "Oh, I thought you meant that you bought it online. But you're talking about one of those home shopping shows, right? Yeah, they're fun."

msgctxt "11700_Erena"
msgid "Right? I seem to end up buying something every time I watch."
msgstr "Right? I seem to end up buying something every time I watch."

msgctxt "11712_Erena"
msgid "Hope it arrives soon. I want it now!"
msgstr "Hope it arrives soon. I want it now!"

msgctxt "11724_Akiyama"
msgid "Uh, you just ordered it, right?"
msgstr "Uh, you just ordered it, right?"

msgctxt "11736_Akiyama"
msgid "Buying the equipment is just the first step. It doesn't necessarily mean you'll become a pro."
msgstr "Buying the equipment is just the first step. It doesn't necessarily mean you'll become a pro."

msgctxt "11748_Erena"
msgid "Yeah, but there're a lotta things that you can only make with a pressure cooker."
msgstr "Yeah, but there're a lotta things that you can only make with a pressure cooker."

msgctxt "11760_Akiyama"
msgid "So what are you going to make?"
msgstr "So what are you going to make?"

msgctxt "11772_Erena"
msgid "Well..."
msgstr "Bueno..."

msgctxt "11784_Erena"
msgid "Cabbage rolls, maybe?"
msgstr "Cabbage rolls, maybe?"

msgctxt "11796_Akiyama"
msgid "Cabbage rolls, huh? Haven't had those in quite a while."
msgstr "Cabbage rolls, huh? Haven't had those in quite a while."

msgctxt "11808_Erena"
msgid "Really? Maybe I can make some for you! This is a chance for you to see how good I really am!"
msgstr "Really? Maybe I can make some for you! This is a chance for you to see how good I really am!"

msgctxt "11820_Akiyama"
msgid "Hmm... I'll be looking forward to it."
msgstr "Hmm... I'll be looking forward to it."

msgctxt "11832_Erena"
msgid "Meh..."
msgstr "Meh..."

msgctxt "11844_Akiyama"
msgid "What's wrong?"
msgstr "¿Qué ocurre?"

msgctxt "11856_Erena"
msgid "Oh, the usual. I'm gettin' kinda sick of him. It's not like it was at the start."
msgstr "Oh, the usual. I'm gettin' kinda sick of him. It's not like it was at the start."

msgctxt "11868_Akiyama"
msgid "Ah. You're talking about that handsome boyfriend of yours?"
msgstr "Ah. You're talking about that handsome boyfriend of yours?"

msgctxt "11880_Erena"
msgid "Actually, now that I've seen him up close for a while, I realized he isn't that handsome."
msgstr "Actually, now that I've seen him up close for a while, I realized he isn't that handsome."

msgctxt "11892_Akiyama"
msgid "Hey! This whole relationship started because you thought he was handsome, and now you don't even think that?"
msgstr "Hey! This whole relationship started because you thought he was handsome, and now you don't even think that?"

msgctxt "11904_Erena"
msgid "I don't like the way he eats. And he tends to mumble, so sometimes I can't tell what he's sayin'."
msgstr "I don't like the way he eats. And he tends to mumble, so sometimes I can't tell what he's sayin'."

msgctxt "11916_Erena"
msgid "I'm just not feeling it anymore..."
msgstr "I'm just not feeling it anymore..."

msgctxt "11928_Akiyama"
msgid "This is your chance to end it. It's better to make a clean break now than to let it drag on forever."
msgstr "This is your chance to end it. It's better to make a clean break now than to let it drag on forever."

msgctxt "11940_Erena"
msgid "Maybe you're right."
msgstr "Tal vez tengas razón."

msgctxt "11952_Akiyama"
msgid "That didn't last long though, did it?"
msgstr "That didn't last long though, did it?"

msgctxt "11964_Erena"
msgid "No, it didn't. Sometimes I really think I'm an idiot."
msgstr "No, it didn't. Sometimes I really think I'm an idiot."

msgctxt "11976_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. Just spend a little longer picking out your next boyfriend, okay?"
msgstr "Heheh. Just spend a little longer picking out your next boyfriend, okay?"

msgctxt "11988_Erena"
msgid "I will."
msgstr "Lo haré."

msgctxt "12000_Erena"
msgid "I know! Maybe you can be my next boyfriend!?"
msgstr "I know! Maybe you can be my next boyfriend!?"

msgctxt "12012_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. I'm not sure I want to go out with somebody who has such bad taste in men."
msgstr "Heheh. I'm not sure I want to go out with somebody who has such bad taste in men."

msgctxt "12024_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah!"
msgstr "Hahahah!"

msgctxt "12036_Akiyama"
msgid "Do you know how he feels? Maybe he's madly in love with you."
msgstr "Do you know how he feels? Maybe he's madly in love with you."

msgctxt "12048_Erena"
msgid "I don't know... Actually, I never really thought about it."
msgstr "I don't know... Actually, I never really thought about it."

msgctxt "12060_Akiyama"
msgid "Why not?"
msgstr "¿Por qué no?"

msgctxt "12072_Erena"
msgid "If I really like somebody, it don't really matter if they like me or not."
msgstr "If I really like somebody, it don't really matter if they like me or not."

msgctxt "12084_Akiyama"
msgid "You're happy just to be near them?"
msgstr "You're happy just to be near them?"

msgctxt "12096_Erena"
msgid "Exactly!"
msgstr "Exactly!"

msgctxt "12108_Erena"
msgid "But I don't think he likes me that much. At least, that's what it feels like."
msgstr "But I don't think he likes me that much. At least, that's what it feels like."

msgctxt "12120_Akiyama"
msgid "I see..."
msgstr "Ya veo..."

msgctxt "12132_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe it's just temporary. It's natural to have ups and downs in any relationship."
msgstr "Maybe it's just temporary. It's natural to have ups and downs in any relationship."

msgctxt "12144_Erena"
msgid "Yeah, but isn't that about couples who've been together for a long time?"
msgstr "Yeah, but isn't that about couples who've been together for a long time?"

msgctxt "12156_Erena"
msgid "We only just started going out recently."
msgstr "We only just started going out recently."

msgctxt "12168_Akiyama"
msgid "Then what is it? Do you think you two just aren't cut out for each other?"
msgstr "Then what is it? Do you think you two just aren't cut out for each other?"

msgctxt "12180_Erena"
msgid "Lately, all I've been thinkin' is, \"I didn't think he was this kind of guy before we started going out.\""
msgstr "Lately, all I've been thinkin' is, \"I didn't think he was this kind of guy before we started going out.\""

msgctxt "12192_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, he just picked you up off the street though, right? How could you have known what kind of guy he was?"
msgstr "Well, he just picked you up off the street though, right? How could you have known what kind of guy he was?"

msgctxt "12204_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! I guess you're right. Maybe this'll be a lesson for me."
msgstr "Hahahah! I guess you're right. Maybe this'll be a lesson for me."

msgctxt "12216_Akiyama"
msgid "Yeah, maybe you should spend a little longer choosing a boyfriend next time."
msgstr "Yeah, maybe you should spend a little longer choosing a boyfriend next time."

msgctxt "12228_Erena"
msgid "Um, I broke up with my boyfriend."
msgstr "Um, I broke up with my boyfriend."

msgctxt "12240_Akiyama"
msgid "I see."
msgstr "Ya veo."

msgctxt "12252_Erena"
msgid "I figured if we were gonna break up sooner or later, it'd be better to get it over with. So I just went ahead and told him."
msgstr "I figured if we were gonna break up sooner or later, it'd be better to get it over with. So I just went ahead and told him."

msgctxt "12264_Erena"
msgid "Apparently he was thinking the same thing."
msgstr "Apparently he was thinking the same thing."

msgctxt "12276_Akiyama"
msgid "Sounds like it was the best decision for both of you."
msgstr "Sounds like it was the best decision for both of you."

msgctxt "12288_Erena"
msgid "Maybe..."
msgstr "Tal vez..."

msgctxt "12300_Akiyama"
msgid "There's no need to be sad about it. That's the way life is. I'm sure you'll meet someone new soon."
msgstr "There's no need to be sad about it. That's the way life is. I'm sure you'll meet someone new soon."

msgctxt "12312_Erena"
msgid "You're so mature. I think it's going to take more time for me to get over this."
msgstr "You're so mature. I think it's going to take more time for me to get over this."

msgctxt "12324_Akiyama"
msgid "That's okay. Take your time. I'm not saying you have to start looking for a new love right away."
msgstr "That's okay. Take your time. I'm not saying you have to start looking for a new love right away."

msgctxt "12336_Akiyama"
msgid "You have to move at your own pace."
msgstr "You have to move at your own pace."

msgctxt "12348_Erena"
msgid "Okay..."
msgstr "Bueno..."

msgctxt "12360_Akiyama"
msgid " Just remember that I'm here if you ever need to talk to somebody."
msgstr " Just remember that I'm here if you ever need to talk to somebody."

msgctxt "12372_Erena"
msgid "Thanks for worrying about me."
msgstr "Thanks for worrying about me."

msgctxt "12384_Akiyama"
msgid "Are you sure you didn't love him? Sometimes you don't really appreciate what you have until it's gone."
msgstr "Are you sure you didn't love him? Sometimes you don't really appreciate what you have until it's gone."

msgctxt "12396_Erena"
msgid "Well, I don't know... I didn't hate him. And the reason I was with him in the first place was because I liked him."
msgstr "Well, I don't know... I didn't hate him. And the reason I was with him in the first place was because I liked him."

msgctxt "12408_Erena"
msgid "I'm not sure if breakin' up was the right thing to do."
msgstr "I'm not sure if breakin' up was the right thing to do."

msgctxt "12420_Akiyama"
msgid "This isn't something that you can know the answer to right away. You have to let some time pass to be able to look at things objectively."
msgstr "This isn't something that you can know the answer to right away. You have to let some time pass to be able to look at things objectively."

msgctxt "12432_Erena"
msgid "I guess you're right..."
msgstr "Supongo que tiene razón..."

msgctxt "12444_Erena"
msgid "Sorry. I'll probably be like this for a while. I hope it won't be too depressing for you."
msgstr "Sorry. I'll probably be like this for a while. I hope it won't be too depressing for you."

msgctxt "12456_Akiyama"
msgid "Don't worry about it."
msgstr "No hay de que."

msgctxt "12468_Akiyama"
msgid "You jumped into that relationship too quickly. You should've waited until you knew a little more about each other before going out."
msgstr "You jumped into that relationship too quickly. You should've waited until you knew a little more about each other before going out."

msgctxt "12480_Erena"
msgid "But then we'd have never gone out. Ain't that right?"
msgstr "But then we'd have never gone out. Ain't that right?"

msgctxt "12492_Akiyama"
msgid "Well... I suppose that's one way to look at it."
msgstr "Well... I suppose that's one way to look at it."

msgctxt "12504_Erena"
msgid "Then it don't matter if you jump into a relationship."
msgstr "Then it don't matter if you jump into a relationship."

msgctxt "12516_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe, but I can't help but think that going out with a guy who picks you up off the street isn't the best idea."
msgstr "Maybe, but I can't help but think that going out with a guy who picks you up off the street isn't the best idea."

msgctxt "12528_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I'm not so sure about that. I know people who started going out that way and got married."
msgstr "Oh, I'm not so sure about that. I know people who started going out that way and got married."

msgctxt "12540_Erena"
msgid "I really don't like the way you're assumin' that I'm the one at fault here."
msgstr "I really don't like the way you're assumin' that I'm the one at fault here."

msgctxt "12552_Erena"
msgid "Now I'm afraid to get involved with someone again..."
msgstr "Now I'm afraid to get involved with someone again..."

msgctxt "12564_Akiyama"
msgid "Why? People break up all the time."
msgstr "Why? People break up all the time."

msgctxt "12576_Erena"
msgid "Yeah, but if it's always going to be like this..."
msgstr "Yeah, but if it's always going to be like this..."

msgctxt "12588_Akiyama"
msgid "Like what?"
msgstr "Un sueño..."

msgctxt "12600_Erena"
msgid "Always worrying about what the other person is thinking. Not being able to be yourself. I just end up gettin' sick of it after a while."
msgstr "Always worrying about what the other person is thinking. Not being able to be yourself. I just end up gettin' sick of it after a while."

msgctxt "12612_Akiyama"
msgid "I see..."
msgstr "Ya veo..."

msgctxt "12624_Erena"
msgid "I'm afraid it'll just be the same if I get involved with somebody else."
msgstr "I'm afraid it'll just be the same if I get involved with somebody else."

msgctxt "12636_Akiyama"
msgid "Don't worry about what the other person thinks. You should just be yourself."
msgstr "Don't worry about what the other person thinks. You should just be yourself."

msgctxt "12648_Erena"
msgid "That's easy to say, but I always end up wantin' to change myself to please whoever I'm seeing."
msgstr "That's easy to say, but I always end up wantin' to change myself to please whoever I'm seeing."

msgctxt "12660_Akiyama"
msgid "That might be okay to some degree, but I think you take it a little too far."
msgstr "That might be okay to some degree, but I think you take it a little too far."

msgctxt "12672_Akiyama"
msgid "If he doesn't like you for who you really are, you're never going to have a real future."
msgstr "If he doesn't like you for who you really are, you're never going to have a real future."

msgctxt "12684_Erena"
msgid "Ya think so? I've never been in a long-term relationship, so I don't know."
msgstr "Ya think so? I've never been in a long-term relationship, so I don't know."

msgctxt "12696_Akiyama"
msgid "Then why don't you give it a try next time?"
msgstr "Then why don't you give it a try next time?"

msgctxt "12708_Erena"
msgid "Alright. I think I will."
msgstr "Alright. I think I will."

msgctxt "12720_Akiyama"
msgid "So what are you saying? You plan to be alone for the rest of your life?"
msgstr "So what are you saying? You plan to be alone for the rest of your life?"

msgctxt "12732_Erena"
msgid "Right now that don't sound so bad."
msgstr "Right now that don't sound so bad."

msgctxt "12744_Akiyama"
msgid "Seriously?"
msgstr "¿En serio?"

msgctxt "12756_Erena"
msgid "I'm just so sick of it all. Maybe I should just stick to relationships like the ones I got with my customers here. It's not as tiring."
msgstr "I'm just so sick of it all. Maybe I should just stick to relationships like the ones I got with my customers here. It's not as tiring."

msgctxt "12768_Akiyama"
msgid "Look, you're a little down right now, but I know you're going to want to have another relationship sooner or later. Cheer up."
msgstr "Look, you're a little down right now, but I know you're going to want to have another relationship sooner or later. Cheer up."

msgctxt "12780_Erena"
msgid "Maybe you're right, but I don't really want to talk about it right now. Sorry, but do you mind if we change the subject?"
msgstr "Maybe you're right, but I don't really want to talk about it right now. Sorry, but do you mind if we change the subject?"

msgctxt "12792_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh... Okay then."
msgstr "Oh... Okay then."

msgctxt "12804_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe the opposite would be better."
msgstr "Maybe the opposite would be better."

msgctxt "12816_Erena"
msgid "The opposite?"
msgstr "The opposite?"

msgctxt "12828_Akiyama"
msgid "I mean, maybe it would be better if you could find a guy who'd change to suit you."
msgstr "I mean, maybe it would be better if you could find a guy who'd change to suit you."

msgctxt "12840_Akiyama"
msgid "Either that, or find somebody that you can just be yourself with."
msgstr "Either that, or find somebody that you can just be yourself with."

msgctxt "12852_Erena"
msgid "Well... That'd definitely be less tiring for me."
msgstr "Well... That'd definitely be less tiring for me."

msgctxt "12864_Akiyama"
msgid "In any case, why don't you stop going to such lengths to try and please people?"
msgstr "In any case, why don't you stop going to such lengths to try and please people?"

msgctxt "12876_Erena"
msgid "Yeah... I'll try."
msgstr "Yeah... I'll try."

msgctxt "12888_Erena"
msgid "Thanks for listenin'."
msgstr "Thanks for listenin'."

msgctxt "12900_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh."
msgstr "Je, je, je."

msgctxt "12912_Erena"
msgid "I saw the best romantic comedy yesterday!"
msgstr "I saw the best romantic comedy yesterday!"

msgctxt "12924_Akiyama"
msgid "You like those?"
msgstr "You like those?"

msgctxt "12936_Erena"
msgid "I guess. I like horror, too, but the girl in me can't get enough romantic comedies."
msgstr "I guess. I like horror, too, but the girl in me can't get enough romantic comedies."

msgctxt "12948_Erena"
msgid "I love stories with happy endings. <Color:7>♥<Color:Default>"
msgstr "I love stories with happy endings. <Color:7>♥<Color:Default>"

msgctxt "12960_Akiyama"
msgid "I see."
msgstr "Ya veo."

msgctxt "12972_Erena"
msgid "You know, movies where the guy and the girl keep missing each other, but finally get together at the end?"
msgstr "You know, movies where the guy and the girl keep missing each other, but finally get together at the end?"

msgctxt "12984_Erena"
msgid "So romantic! Don't you just love that kinda thing?"
msgstr "So romantic! Don't you just love that kinda thing?"

msgctxt "12996_Akiyama"
msgid "Real life never works out that way. If you keep missing each other, you probably won't end up like that."
msgstr "Real life never works out that way. If you keep missing each other, you probably won't end up like that."

msgctxt "13008_Erena"
msgid "Why do ya have to be so cynical?"
msgstr "Why do ya have to be so cynical?"

msgctxt "13020_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe it's because I'm a man, but I've always been that way. Sometimes I want to scream at the screen because the plot's so unrealistic."
msgstr "Maybe it's because I'm a man, but I've always been that way. Sometimes I want to scream at the screen because the plot's so unrealistic."

msgctxt "13032_Erena"
msgid "If I were watchin' a movie and someone did that, I'd get pretty upset."
msgstr "If I were watchin' a movie and someone did that, I'd get pretty upset."

msgctxt "13044_Erena"
msgid "I think I need a more romantic type of man."
msgstr "I think I need a more romantic type of man."

msgctxt "13056_Akiyama"
msgid "I don't like happy endings. Maybe I'm just the twisted type."
msgstr "I don't like happy endings. Maybe I'm just the twisted type."

msgctxt "13068_Erena"
msgid "Really? What kind of movies do you like?"
msgstr "Really? What kind of movies do you like?"

msgctxt "13080_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, more realistic stuff, I guess. You know, people doing the best they can, even if it doesn't end well."
msgstr "Well, more realistic stuff, I guess. You know, people doing the best they can, even if it doesn't end well."

msgctxt "13092_Erena"
msgid "I see. Why do you think you like that?"
msgstr "I see. Why do you think you like that?"

msgctxt "13104_Akiyama"
msgid "Maybe it's because of my job. I get to see how lots of different kinds of people live. I know that life can be hard."
msgstr "Maybe it's because of my job. I get to see how lots of different kinds of people live. I know that life can be hard."

msgctxt "13116_Erena"
msgid "Hmm... That sounds convincing coming from an older gentleman.\\r\n"\n" But I think I'll stick with my romantic comedies for the moment."
msgstr "Hmm... That sounds convincing coming from an older gentleman.\\r\n"\n" But I think I'll stick with my romantic comedies for the moment."

msgctxt "13128_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh."
msgstr "Je, je, je."

msgctxt "13140_Akiyama"
msgid "You're pretty cute sometimes."
msgstr "You're pretty cute sometimes."

msgctxt "13152_Erena"
msgid "I know."
msgstr "Lo sé."

msgctxt "13164_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. But don't you sometimes know exactly how a story's going to end, right when it starts?"
msgstr "Heheh. But don't you sometimes know exactly how a story's going to end, right when it starts?"

msgctxt "13176_Akiyama"
msgid "It's not like the two main characters aren't going to get together, right?"
msgstr "It's not like the two main characters aren't going to get together, right?"

msgctxt "13188_Erena"
msgid "That's okay. It's not the ending that's important. It's how they get there, how they overcome the obstacles in front of them."
msgstr "That's okay. It's not the ending that's important. It's how they get there, how they overcome the obstacles in front of them."

msgctxt "13200_Akiyama"
msgid "Hmm... I haven't thought about it that way."
msgstr "Hmm... I haven't thought about it that way."

msgctxt "13212_Erena"
msgid "I've never met a man like you before."
msgstr "I've never met a man like you before."

msgctxt "13224_Akiyama"
msgid "Really?"
msgstr "¿De verdad?"

msgctxt "13236_Erena"
msgid "Yeah. Don't know what it is, but I really feel like I can be myself in front of you."
msgstr "Yeah. Don't know what it is, but I really feel like I can be myself in front of you."

msgctxt "13248_Akiyama"
msgid "That's nice of you to say."
msgstr "That's nice of you to say."

msgctxt "13260_Erena"
msgid "I feel like you accept me for who I am."
msgstr "I feel like you accept me for who I am."

msgctxt "13272_Erena"
msgid "That's why I can talk to you about anything. You've really given me a lot of good advice."
msgstr "That's why I can talk to you about anything. You've really given me a lot of good advice."

msgctxt "13284_Akiyama"
msgid "You can't do that with other customers? Why don't you try being yourself with everyone?"
msgstr "You can't do that with other customers? Why don't you try being yourself with everyone?"

msgctxt "13296_Erena"
msgid "But I always have to leave a good impression on my customers. I can't talk about my private life."
msgstr "But I always have to leave a good impression on my customers. I can't talk about my private life."

msgctxt "13308_Akiyama"
msgid "But you do with me."
msgstr "But you do with me."

msgctxt "13320_Erena"
msgid "Is that a problem?"
msgstr "Is that a problem?"

msgctxt "13332_Akiyama"
msgid "A problem? Not at all. The fact that you feel you can talk about personal things with me shows that you trust me."
msgstr "A problem? Not at all. The fact that you feel you can talk about personal things with me shows that you trust me."

msgctxt "13344_Erena"
msgid "Really?"
msgstr "¿De verdad?"

msgctxt "13356_Akiyama"
msgid "Yeah."
msgstr "Sí."

msgctxt "13368_Erena"
msgid "Thank you. You're so sweet. I love that about you."
msgstr "Thank you. You're so sweet. I love that about you."

msgctxt "13380_Erena"
msgid "But I should try and be more independent, and not rely on you all the time."
msgstr "But I should try and be more independent, and not rely on you all the time."

msgctxt "13392_Akiyama"
msgid "We do get along well, don't we? For some reason I feel really relaxed when I talk with you."
msgstr "We do get along well, don't we? For some reason I feel really relaxed when I talk with you."

msgctxt "13404_Erena"
msgid "Really!? That's great!"
msgstr "Really!? That's great!"

msgctxt "13416_Erena"
msgid "I know! If you got any problems that you can't discuss with other people, you can tell me!"
msgstr "I know! If you got any problems that you can't discuss with other people, you can tell me!"

msgctxt "13428_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, I don't really have anything to say right now."
msgstr "Well, I don't really have anything to say right now."

msgctxt "13440_Erena"
msgid "There's no reason to hide anything from me. Come on, tell me your deepest, darkest secrets!"
msgstr "There's no reason to hide anything from me. Come on, tell me your deepest, darkest secrets!"

msgctxt "13452_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, brother."
msgstr "Oh, vamos hermano."

msgctxt "13464_Akiyama"
msgid "I'm nobody special. I haven't really done anything for you."
msgstr "I'm nobody special. I haven't really done anything for you."

msgctxt "13476_Erena"
msgid "What? Why'd you say that?"
msgstr "What? Why'd you say that?"

msgctxt "13488_Erena"
msgid "Here I am, telling you that you've helped me out a lot, and you go and brush it off like it means nothin'. Guess ya don't give a crap about me, huh?"
msgstr "Here I am, telling you that you've helped me out a lot, and you go and brush it off like it means nothin'. Guess ya don't give a crap about me, huh?"

msgctxt "13500_Akiyama"
msgid "I just meant that I'm sure you would've made it through on your own, even if I hadn't been here. All I've done is listen to you."
msgstr "I just meant that I'm sure you would've made it through on your own, even if I hadn't been here. All I've done is listen to you."

msgctxt "13512_Erena"
msgid "You mean I've just been foolin' myself all this time? I thought we had a connection... Guess it was all in my head. Talk about disappointing."
msgstr "You mean I've just been foolin' myself all this time? I thought we had a connection... Guess it was all in my head. Talk about disappointing."

msgctxt "13524_Akiyama"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "13536_Erena"
msgid "Do you know much about LA?"
msgstr "Do you know much about LA?"

msgctxt "13548_Akiyama"
msgid "You mean Los Angeles?"
msgstr "You mean Los Angeles?"

msgctxt "13560_Akiyama"
msgid "Not really. I don't know much about foreign countries. Why do you ask?"
msgstr "Not really. I don't know much about foreign countries. Why do you ask?"

msgctxt "13572_Erena"
msgid "One of my cousins is there right now, and I just thought it'd be cool to visit him someday."
msgstr "One of my cousins is there right now, and I just thought it'd be cool to visit him someday."

msgctxt "13584_Akiyama"
msgid "Why not? Sounds like it could be fun."
msgstr "Why not? Sounds like it could be fun."

msgctxt "13596_Erena"
msgid "But I can't go right away. Plus, I also want to go to Hawaii sometime."
msgstr "But I can't go right away. Plus, I also want to go to Hawaii sometime."

msgctxt "13608_Akiyama"
msgid "You could do both. You could fly to LA, then go back via Hawaii."
msgstr "You could do both. You could fly to LA, then go back via Hawaii."

msgctxt "13620_Erena"
msgid "Guess that's an option... But I've always wanted to go to Guam, too."
msgstr "Guess that's an option... But I've always wanted to go to Guam, too."

msgctxt "13632_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, I guess you could go to LA, then Hawaii, and stop by Guam on the way home."
msgstr "Well, I guess you could go to LA, then Hawaii, and stop by Guam on the way home."

msgctxt "13644_Erena"
msgid "Are you teasing me?"
msgstr "Are you teasing me?"

msgctxt "13656_Akiyama"
msgid "Huh?"
msgstr "Uh, ¿y eso?"

msgctxt "13668_Erena"
msgid "I mean, that's impossible. You're obviously just bein' mean."
msgstr "I mean, that's impossible. You're obviously just bein' mean."

msgctxt "13680_Akiyama"
msgid "Sorry..."
msgstr "Lo siento..."

msgctxt "13692_Akiyama"
msgid "Where else do you want to visit? You seem eager to travel."
msgstr "Where else do you want to visit? You seem eager to travel."

msgctxt "13704_Erena"
msgid "Well... I've always wanted to see Guam."
msgstr "Well... I've always wanted to see Guam."

msgctxt "13716_Akiyama"
msgid "Guam? Isn't Hawaii good enough?"
msgstr "Guam? Isn't Hawaii good enough?"

msgctxt "13728_Erena"
msgid "I guess I just can't get enough of the tropics."
msgstr "I guess I just can't get enough of the tropics."

msgctxt "13740_Akiyama"
msgid "Since you're being so extravagant, why don't you go to Bali and Fiji while you're at it?"
msgstr "Since you're being so extravagant, why don't you go to Bali and Fiji while you're at it?"

msgctxt "13752_Erena"
msgid "Hahahah! Maybe I should just make it a trip around the world. I know! You could take me!"
msgstr "Hahahah! Maybe I should just make it a trip around the world. I know! You could take me!"

msgctxt "13764_Akiyama"
msgid "Whoa, don't get carried away there."
msgstr "Whoa, don't get carried away there."

msgctxt "13776_Akiyama"
msgid "Wouldn't it be better to just travel in Japan? I personally don't like trips where your schedule is all packed."
msgstr "Wouldn't it be better to just travel in Japan? I personally don't like trips where your schedule is all packed."

msgctxt "13788_Akiyama"
msgid "Relaxing at a hot spring somewhere in Japan would be more my speed."
msgstr "Relaxing at a hot spring somewhere in Japan would be more my speed."

msgctxt "13800_Erena"
msgid "Ooh, hot springs are nice, too."
msgstr "Ooh, hot springs are nice, too."

msgctxt "13812_Akiyama"
msgid "Do they have hot springs in Kyoto?"
msgstr "Do they have hot springs in Kyoto?"

msgctxt "13824_Erena"
msgid "Well, yes. Places like Ohara and Arashiyama."
msgstr "Well, yes. Places like Ohara and Arashiyama."

msgctxt "13836_Akiyama"
msgid "I wouldn't mind visiting there sometime."
msgstr "I wouldn't mind visiting there sometime."

msgctxt "13848_Erena"
msgid "Really? I'd love to go, too!"
msgstr "Really? I'd love to go, too!"

msgctxt "13860_Akiyama"
msgid "Huh? You're coming, too? How am I supposed to relax then?"
msgstr "Huh? You're coming, too? How am I supposed to relax then?"

msgctxt "13872_Erena"
msgid "My sister got real mad at me recently."
msgstr "My sister got real mad at me recently."

msgctxt "13884_Akiyama"
msgid "What did you do?"
msgstr "What did you do?"

msgctxt "13896_Erena"
msgid "The problem is I did nothing. Literally. I mean, I didn't clean up the apartment."
msgstr "The problem is I did nothing. Literally. I mean, I didn't clean up the apartment."

msgctxt "13908_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh, I understand that. I never clean."
msgstr "Oh, I understand that. I never clean."

msgctxt "13920_Erena"
msgid "You too? My sister can be such a pain about it."
msgstr "You too? My sister can be such a pain about it."

msgctxt "13932_Akiyama"
msgid "But you're the one who got the place dirty in the first place, right?"
msgstr "But you're the one who got the place dirty in the first place, right?"

msgctxt "13944_Erena"
msgid "Well..."
msgstr "Bueno..."

msgctxt "13956_Erena"
msgid "Yes."
msgstr "Sí."

msgctxt "13968_Akiyama"
msgid "I thought so. Then she's right."
msgstr "I thought so. Then she's right."

msgctxt "13980_Erena"
msgid "But she's so annoying about it."
msgstr "But she's so annoying about it."

msgctxt "13992_Akiyama"
msgid "How annoying is she, exactly?"
msgstr "How annoying is she, exactly?"

msgctxt "14004_Erena"
msgid "Very?"
msgstr "Very?"

msgctxt "14016_Akiyama"
msgid "Is that all?"
msgstr "¿Eso es todo?"

msgctxt "14028_Erena"
msgid "Yeah. She's very annoying."
msgstr "Yeah. She's very annoying."

msgctxt "14040_Akiyama"
msgid "Would it kill you to be a little more descriptive?"
msgstr "Would it kill you to be a little more descriptive?"

msgctxt "14052_Erena"
msgid "But it's true! She's <Italic>very</Italic> annoying!"
msgstr "But it's true! She's <Italic>very</Italic> annoying!"

msgctxt "14064_Akiyama"
msgid "I understand what you mean, but..."
msgstr "I understand what you mean, but..."

msgctxt "14076_Erena"
msgid "Ugh, you're just like my sister. Why do people get so upset about the littlest things?"
msgstr "Ugh, you're just like my sister. Why do people get so upset about the littlest things?"

msgctxt "14088_Akiyama"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "14100_Akiyama"
msgid "When you live together, you have to get along. She came all the way here to Tokyo, right?"
msgstr "When you live together, you have to get along. She came all the way here to Tokyo, right?"

msgctxt "14112_Erena"
msgid "That's true. But it isn't like we don't ever get along."
msgstr "That's true. But it isn't like we don't ever get along."

msgctxt "14124_Erena"
msgid "It's just that we occasionally－very occasionally－have a horrible fight."
msgstr "It's just that we occasionally－very occasionally－have a horrible fight."

msgctxt "14136_Akiyama"
msgid "That happens when you live together. It probably wouldn't matter who it was."
msgstr "That happens when you live together. It probably wouldn't matter who it was."

msgctxt "14148_Erena"
msgid "Yeah."
msgstr "Sí."

msgctxt "14160_Erena"
msgid "I know! We could have separate rooms! Then she won't be able to complain about what I do in my own room!"
msgstr "I know! We could have separate rooms! Then she won't be able to complain about what I do in my own room!"

msgctxt "14172_Akiyama"
msgid "Do you have room for that?"
msgstr "Do you have room for that?"

msgctxt "14184_Erena"
msgid "Well, no. We'd have to move."
msgstr "Well, no. We'd have to move."

msgctxt "14196_Akiyama"
msgid "Don't you think cleaning up would be easier than moving?"
msgstr "Don't you think cleaning up would be easier than moving?"

msgctxt "14208_Erena"
msgid "Oh, I guess... Ugh, what a pain."
msgstr "Oh, I guess... Ugh, what a pain."

msgctxt "14220_Akiyama"
msgid "Why doesn't she just clean up? If she spent her time cleaning instead of complaining, the place would be spotless."
msgstr "Why doesn't she just clean up? If she spent her time cleaning instead of complaining, the place would be spotless."

msgctxt "14232_Erena"
msgid "I like the way ya think!"
msgstr "I like the way ya think!"

msgctxt "14244_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh."
msgstr "Je, je, je."

msgctxt "14256_Erena"
msgid "But my sister's busy with work. I don't want to cause more trouble for her."
msgstr "But my sister's busy with work. I don't want to cause more trouble for her."

msgctxt "14268_Erena"
msgid "I guess I've got to try and be neater."
msgstr "I guess I've got to try and be neater."

msgctxt "14280_Akiyama"
msgid "You can do it."
msgstr "You can do it."

msgctxt "14292_Erena"
msgid "You really think so?"
msgstr "¿De verdad crees eso...?"

msgctxt "14304_Akiyama"
msgid "Sure. Why don't you try surprising her?"
msgstr "Sure. Why don't you try surprising her?"

msgctxt "14316_Erena"
msgid "  That might be fun. I can just imagine the look on her face if I started cleanin' up all of a sudden."
msgstr "  That might be fun. I can just imagine the look on her face if I started cleanin' up all of a sudden."

msgctxt "14328_Erena"
msgid "Alright. I'll do it!"
msgstr "Alright. I'll do it!"

msgctxt "14340_Erena"
msgid "A friend of mine got married the other day."
msgstr "A friend of mine got married the other day."

msgctxt "14352_Erena"
msgid "She was so pretty in her wedding dress! The groom was... Well, he was okay."
msgstr "She was so pretty in her wedding dress! The groom was... Well, he was okay."

msgctxt "14364_Erena"
msgid "But the bride! She was practically glowin'! I was so jealous!"
msgstr "But the bride! She was practically glowin'! I was so jealous!"

msgctxt "14376_Akiyama"
msgid "Heheh. You'll get your chance someday."
msgstr "Heheh. You'll get your chance someday."

msgctxt "14388_Erena"
msgid "Maybe... I never really used to dream about getting married."
msgstr "Maybe... I never really used to dream about getting married."

msgctxt "14400_Erena"
msgid "But that all changed when I saw my friend's wedding. Now I'm thinkin' about the kind of dress I want, and the kind of ceremony I'd have."
msgstr "But that all changed when I saw my friend's wedding. Now I'm thinkin' about the kind of dress I want, and the kind of ceremony I'd have."

msgctxt "14412_Akiyama"
msgid "Sounds like you're itching to get hitched."
msgstr "Sounds like you're itching to get hitched."

msgctxt "14424_Erena"
msgid "But of course I got no one to get married to. I am not sure there's anybody out there who'd want to marry somebody like me."
msgstr "But of course I got no one to get married to. I am not sure there's anybody out there who'd want to marry somebody like me."

msgctxt "14436_Erena"
msgid "I'm so impatient. And even though I got the looks, I'm real lazy."
msgstr "I'm so impatient. And even though I got the looks, I'm real lazy."

msgctxt "14448_Erena"
msgid "But I don't want to sit around doin' the same thing over and over again, either."
msgstr "But I don't want to sit around doin' the same thing over and over again, either."

msgctxt "14460_Akiyama"
msgid "You don't have anything to worry about."
msgstr "You don't have anything to worry about."

msgctxt "14472_Erena"
msgid "Really? You think somebody would want to marry me?"
msgstr "Really? You think somebody would want to marry me?"

msgctxt "14484_Akiyama"
msgid "Sure. Probably."
msgstr "Sure. Probably."

msgctxt "14496_Erena"
msgid "Probably? You don't sound real confident. Hey, what about you?"
msgstr "Probably? You don't sound real confident. Hey, what about you?"

msgctxt "14508_Akiyama"
msgid "What?"
msgstr "¿Qué?"

msgctxt "14520_Erena"
msgid "You're getting older, too. Do you plan to stay single for the rest of your life?"
msgstr "You're getting older, too. Do you plan to stay single for the rest of your life?"

msgctxt "14532_Akiyama"
msgid "I wouldn't mind. I like being alone."
msgstr "I wouldn't mind. I like being alone."

msgctxt "14544_Erena"
msgid "Of course a handsome man like you shouldn't have any trouble gettin' a girl, even if you're older."
msgstr "Of course a handsome man like you shouldn't have any trouble gettin' a girl, even if you're older."

msgctxt "14556_Erena"
msgid "Ugh... Women really get the short end of the stick."
msgstr "Ugh... Women really get the short end of the stick."

msgctxt "14568_Akiyama"
msgid "Why are you saying all this now? Most girls your age have been thinking about marriage for years."
msgstr "Why are you saying all this now? Most girls your age have been thinking about marriage for years."

msgctxt "14580_Erena"
msgid "Really? Guess if I don't do something soon, it'll be too late for me."
msgstr "Really? Guess if I don't do something soon, it'll be too late for me."

msgctxt "14592_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, there's nothing to panic about. Some women get more attractive as they get older, you know."
msgstr "Well, there's nothing to panic about. Some women get more attractive as they get older, you know."

msgctxt "14604_Erena"
msgid "Y'mean like one of those cougars?"
msgstr "Y'mean like one of those cougars?"

msgctxt "14616_Akiyama"
msgid "You just have to decide what kind of woman you want to be."
msgstr "You just have to decide what kind of woman you want to be."

msgctxt "14628_Erena"
msgid "Guess yer right. I'll start planning right away!"
msgstr "Guess yer right. I'll start planning right away!"

msgctxt "14640_Akiyama"
msgid "You're really worried about this, aren't you? I don't think I've seen you look so serious before."
msgstr "You're really worried about this, aren't you? I don't think I've seen you look so serious before."

msgctxt "14652_Erena"
msgid "Of course I'm worried. Isn't it every girl's dream to get married?"
msgstr "Of course I'm worried. Isn't it every girl's dream to get married?"

msgctxt "14664_Akiyama"
msgid "I suppose so. I'll tell you what. If you haven't found anybody in five years, maybe we can get married."
msgstr "I suppose so. I'll tell you what. If you haven't found anybody in five years, maybe we can get married."

msgctxt "14676_Erena"
msgid "Really!? Are you sure I'm good enough?"
msgstr "Really!? Are you sure I'm good enough?"

msgctxt "14688_Akiyama"
msgid "Wait a minute. Are you saying you're not going to change at all in five years? That could be a problem."
msgstr "Wait a minute. Are you saying you're not going to change at all in five years? That could be a problem."

msgctxt "14700_Erena"
msgid "Huh? Do ya want me or not!?"
msgstr "Huh? Do ya want me or not!?"

msgctxt "14712_Erena"
msgid "I'm so tired..."
msgstr "I'm so tired..."

msgctxt "14724_Akiyama"
msgid "What's the problem?"
msgstr "¿Cuál es el problema?"

msgctxt "14736_Erena"
msgid "I didn't feel like going out, so I holed up in my apartment watching DVDs."
msgstr "I didn't feel like going out, so I holed up in my apartment watching DVDs."

msgctxt "14748_Akiyama"
msgid "There's nothing wrong with that once in a while."
msgstr "There's nothing wrong with that once in a while."

msgctxt "14760_Erena"
msgid "I watched four movies back to back."
msgstr "I watched four movies back to back."

msgctxt "14772_Akiyama"
msgid "That's a lot."
msgstr "That's a lot."

msgctxt "14784_Erena"
msgid "I got hungry in the middle, but it was too much trouble to cook anything, so I just kept watchin'."
msgstr "I got hungry in the middle, but it was too much trouble to cook anything, so I just kept watchin'."

msgctxt "14796_Erena"
msgid "After a while I stopped feeling hungry. I think maybe my stomach got a little flatter."
msgstr "After a while I stopped feeling hungry. I think maybe my stomach got a little flatter."

msgctxt "14808_Akiyama"
msgid "You shouldn't overdo it. If you go too long without eating, it can be a shock to your body when you finally do."
msgstr "You shouldn't overdo it. If you go too long without eating, it can be a shock to your body when you finally do."

msgctxt "14820_Erena"
msgid "Okay..."
msgstr "Bueno..."

msgctxt "14832_Akiyama"
msgid "Are you hungry now?"
msgstr "Are you hungry now?"

msgctxt "14844_Erena"
msgid "Can I order something?"
msgstr "Can I order something?"

msgctxt "14856_Akiyama"
msgid "Sure. Get whatever you like."
msgstr "Sure. Get whatever you like."

msgctxt "14868_Erena"
msgid "Thank you. But I think I'm okay for the moment. I'll have a proper meal later."
msgstr "Thank you. But I think I'm okay for the moment. I'll have a proper meal later."

msgctxt "14880_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh... Okay then."
msgstr "Oh... Okay then."

msgctxt "14892_Akiyama"
msgid "I know a good restaurant you might like. The food isn't very heavy. It should be perfect."
msgstr "I know a good restaurant you might like. The food isn't very heavy. It should be perfect."

msgctxt "14904_Erena"
msgid "Really? What kind of food is it?"
msgstr "Really? What kind of food is it?"

msgctxt "14916_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, I guess you could say it's family style."
msgstr "Well, I guess you could say it's family style."

